text:
since the beginning of this year 20 women were murdered by their husbands, boyfriends or exes.

this terror has to stop.

israel’s government doesn’t do much in order to prevent these tragedies, there are no special programs in schools and not enough boys are getting good father-husband examples at home.

women are left to literally die, because no one gives a damn; not the government, or the media, or even the people, it’s ‘just another woman’ who died from 15 stabs last night.

a couple of weeks ago, i made a commitment to speak up on issues i find important, to use this platform not only to post ootd’s but also to promote and try to correct injustice in it’s different forms.
well, this is one of those injustices.

you can choose to unfollow me, because you really just couldn’t care less, or you can choose to follow me, because fashion, and women’s rights, and art, and pretty coffee spots can mix and match just fine.

if you want to show solidarity, you can join me at the protest rally this thursday at dizengoff square in tel aviv 11am.

#womenslivesmatter #womensupportwomen

text:
even though i knew all the signs i still let everything go on. i thought i was happy and inlove but really i wasn't. i was blinded by the fact i thought he loved me, and when he would do something that upsetted me it was always sorry but then he'd do it again and again. i seen to blame myself for everything that happened because i should of noticed these signs. i was taught about these signs. how did they pass right over my head?

text:
hello! this is my first post, and i’d like to just take a moment and talk about sexual assault. so thousands of people get assaulted on the daily. not just women, men too. of course it’s not as common but it still happeneds. we still need to talk about it. survivors need a safe place to be able to talk about their adults and not feel judged. which oddly enough even in 2018 people are defending rapists that have been proven to be guilty. we live in such a world that it’s so hard for women and men to come forward because they’re scared that they might get death threats, be killed, assaulted again, and an easy target. no more silence. -
-
-
- tags -
-

text:
il y tout juste un an, le 15 octobre 2017, l’actrice alyssa milano lançait le hashtag #metoo pour encourager les femmes à dénoncer les actes d’agression sexuelle et de harcèlement dont elles peuvent être les victimes, notamment dans le milieu professionnel.
——-
ce mouvement fait suite aux accusations portées à l’encontre du producteur harvey weinstein soupçonné d’avoir profité de sa position pour abuser de plusieurs femmes. ——-
cette initiative a permis à de nombreuses femmes de trouver un espace d’expression pour dénoncer les violences dont elles sont victimes.
——-
récemment l’ouverture du blog #metooep, rappelle que le harcèlement est encore loin d’avoir était banni, y compris dans les grandes institutions.
#metoo #histoireimmediate #histoire #casestpassele

text:
through our whole relationship, i was told what i should do or how i should do things. i had to post him as mcm. whenever we were together we had to show we were in a relationship such as him putting his arm around my shoulders, kissing me, holding my hand, etc. it was constant touching and hanging on me. he would get so angery at the littlest things and guilt me. his favorite line was "you dont like me then" all signs of domestic violence that i failed to notice. when i would tell people about it i would be told, "well that's how boys are," or, " he "loves" me." how could he love me when every little thing i did he had to watch? why would he get so mad at someone he loves?

text: corinne : «quand j’avais 25 ans, pendant que je dormais, quelqu’un est entré chez moi par infraction et m’a agressée sexuellement... quand ça m’est arrivé, je me suis dit qu’à part la mort, y’avait pas grand-chose de pire que ça. après l’agression, ça a été une pente descendante. j’ai perdu du poids, j’ai arrêté de manger, de dormir et de travailler pendant une période…j’étais mal tout le temps. j’ai consommé excessivement parce que je croyais que ça allait m’aider à arrêter d’avoir peur. toute ma vie était basée autour de ça; la peur d’avoir peur. ça a déconstruit ma vie et je suis devenue complètement dépendante des autres. mais petit à petit, j’ai commencé à remonter la pente et à me faire confiance à nouveau. ça fait 15 ans que je suis en thérapie et j’ai arrêté de consommer y’a bien longtemps. la maternité m’a permis de m’accrocher à la vie et de retrouver une certaine paix intérieure. mon fils a 6 ans, c’est mon soleil. il me comble de joie et me ramène à l’essentiel malgré la solitude d’être une mère monoparentale. la course m’a aussi vraiment aidée et m’aide encore aujourd’hui. ça me permet de libérer toutes les émotions qui sont bloquées en moi. mais, j’ai réalisé cette année que j’avais beau courir trois fois par semaine et faire toutes les thérapies du monde…je ne serai pas capable de tout guérir. il y a des choses qui restent quand tu fais un choc post-traumatique. je me sens toujours en état d’hypervigilance et je fais aussi beaucoup d’insomnie. ça a été vraiment difficile parce que l’agresseur est encore en liberté… ils ne l’ont jamais retrouvé. mais à un moment donné, j’ai arrêté de résister et de vouloir tout régler. j’ai accepté que j’allais être une personne anxieuse toute ma vie. ça m’empêche pas de dire que je me sens heureuse aujourd’hui et que j’ai le sentiment de m’en être sortie. je suis rendue à un point où je ne suis plus du tout dans la honte, mais dans l’acceptation et le pardon. je ne me sens plus comme une victime et je suis fière de la femme que je suis devenue. à mes yeux, c’est mon plus bel accomplissement. je souhaite que mon partage aide d’autres femmes à se libérer de la honte qu’elles peuvent ressentir. »#yourenotalone #metoo

text:
#diaryofasimplelagosoap 
episode 40: 15/10/2018. 
@rsdushers.  @ladycath_.  @arewasunshyne.  @yougetmouth.

it's fela kuti's birthday. anthony joshua's as well. plus ginuwine, keyshia cole, tito jackson and jack ma. significant day for many as well. the #metoo movement began exactly a year ago, thomas sankara was killed today, divorces, marriages - a lot happened in history today and you can catch up via twitter @yougetmouth. 
today began normally - transportation stress, etc. got to the office almost three hours after i left home. crazy. the weird looks some people give me on the bus and streets though, like they're trying to figure out where they've seen the face yet are pretty sure the person they think it is isn't me. well, everyday is no make-up day for me - unless i'm on wakeupnigeria. thankfully not today. 😆 
radio went smoothly. i hit a jackpot - both ibk and esther on the news. 😎 i literally raced out of the studio to meet a deadline, only to encounter a nasty hitch. at least i eventually got home safe... when i was leaving the office though, i found it perturbing that there was nocontinuity . will have to find out what happened tomorrow. 
i hope all went well... bro. wale is on leave. tomorrow is his birthday. if i tell you his age, you won't believe me so i won't even bother. 😂 
sadly, iyahjogbo lost her mother, yesterday. wonderful woman. i still cant believe it. 
i pray not to receive any more death notices this year or anytime soon, in jesus' name. amen. 
may her soul rest in peace. amen. 
it is well. 
i'm craving asian, french and italian cuisine. very much. i really need to indulge soon.😥. please, follow @rsdushers, @ladycath_, @arewasunshyne and @yougetmouth. 
@regran_ed from @yougetmouth -  this oga wan use eye finish our ambassador ..😂 anothr crazy minute with @ladyomary1 ft mimiko..hehe

abeg check out full video here: 
http://yougetmouth.com/a-minute-with-ladyomary-ft-mimiko-the-impresssionist/ - #regrann

text:
it's day 15 of #inktober with the prompt #weak and i decided to do something meaningful even though it's quick. (ooh rhyme) 
most of these are used to demean or shame people, especially girls, telling them they are too much of any of these things. weak is at the top, because that's what we think we are when faced with all these accusations, weakness is what they are meant to make us feel. and yet some are called "too strong", as if that's bad. so the word #strong is at the bottom. and most of these words have their opposite in there too, because usually girls just can't win. either they're too opinionated or too shallow. either too girly or a dyke. either too slutty or a prude. there's nothing they can do without being constantly attacked and criticized. 
in conclusion, it is always hard to exist in a world that hates you for that alone. but withstanding it, learning and growing as a person who can raise awareness and teach others in the same position is what makes you strong.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
trevor noah eloquently breaks down how trump has weaponized victimhood - “he knows how to offer victimhood to people who have the least claim to it” ... “the narrative that has been created is that like ‘oh, these 100 men represent all the men and all men should be afraid of it.’”... “if you can convince men that they're the true victims of the #metoo movement, you get men to fight against a movement that's really about holding men who are doing bad things accountable, as opposed to making all men scapegoats for something that they're not doing... it's such a powerful, gripping thing that trump does really well.” ... “...and he's turned it with everybody. he goes ‘the real victims in the story is not the kids in the cages, it's you —they're coming to take your place.’ ... ‘the real victim isn't the refugee from syria, it's you who's going to get blown up by a terrorist bomb...’"
.
see the whole piece on youtube — https://bit.ly/2qrfbfi

text:
if there's one thing a victim of abuse learns, it's how to "act" like everything is okay. very few people can ever tell when things are not going well. it takes courage and vulnerability to show emotions. when you are in a abusive relationship, emotions equal weakness and weakness is a opportunity for your abuser to  use your emotions against you.  so you learn how to hide everything. you learn how to lie. it's a matter of survival.

help is just a phone call away. make today the day you say enough #changetheending

text:
#metoo - ett år senare

för ett år sedan idag tändes gnistan till de upprop som samlat miljontals kvinnor och brutit tystnadskulturen kring sexuella övergrepp och trakasserier – #metoo.

tänk om vi om ytterligare ett år fick skriva en liknande mening av en rörelse som fick män att samlas och prata om den stereotypa mansrollen; om hur man som man förväntas förhålla sig till kärlek, våld, sårbarhet och sex.

vi på bilda sydväst vill skapa möjligheter för en sådan rörelse – och du kan vara med! i höst skapar vi mötesplatser under namnet #killmiddag. en bra hjälp på vägen till att börja öppna upp och prata om mansroller och jämställdhet, män emellan.

hör av dig till caroline.jornland@bilda.nu om du vill veta mer!

text:
father who raped his newborn daughter and broke her legs is sentenced to 240 years in prison.

a father who raped his newborn daughter and crushed her body so hard that he broke her ribs and legs has been jailed for 240 years.

patricio medina, 27, was in a "meth-fuelled haze" when he sexually assaulted his one-month-old daughter at their home. a court heard the monster father squeezed the girl's ribs, shook her and crushed her body against his so violently he shattered her ribs and legs. 
medina confessed his wicked acts to an inmate in jail ahead of his trial. during the trial, he denied aggravated sexual assault of a child younger than six, two counts of injury to a child and two counts of endangering a child.

but on thursday, he was convicted on each charge and sentenced to three 80-year jail terms in texas, us.

the court heard cops were called to medina's home in waco, texas, in march 2014 after getting a report of abuse to a newborn baby. they found medina high on meth and arrested the dad.

the child's mother, lisa montoya, was also charged with abandoning/endangering a child. the affidavit states she put the child in imminent danger of death, bodily injury or physical or mental impairment by not reporting the abuse to the authorities.

the girl, now aged four, is now said to be "doing well" in the care of a family who adopted her and her two siblings

source: mail online. 
#childabuse #rape #stopit #metoo #stoprape #children #newborn #instastories #merrymen #naijagist #texas #usa #nigeriannews #enditnow #america #jailed #america

text:
for a decade after being sexually assaulted art of freelance alumna claire salvo (@clairesalvo) locked the pain away and remained silent. inspired by the bravery of survivors coming forward in 2016, she finally published her own story. now, she is helping to draw attention to other women’s painful stories through her art.
_
salvo was an art of freelance scholarship recipient in spring of 2018, and during that time worked on her project “me:we”, which uses drawings and text to tell the stories of nine women who have been sexually assaulted. me:we is about community and finding solidarity in a solitary experience.
_
learn more about her project and watch her recent interview at the link in bio.
.
.

text:
today marks one year since the #metoo movement went viral. the ‘me too.’ movement ( @metoomvmt ) was founded in 2006 to help survivors of sexual violence, particularly black women and girls, and other young women of color from low wealth communities, find pathways to healing. the movements vision from the beginning was to address both the dearth in resources for survivors of sexual violence and to build a community of advocates, driven by survivors, who will be at the forefront of creating solutions to interrupt sexual violence in their communities.
#wesupportyou #believesurvivors
.

text:
we women have been taught to ignore our offenders since the beginning. due to which we subconsciously wear a smile to cover the states of time where we've been frightened, threatened, forced,  coerced and abused by power. power in all kinds of strange forms. the result is that some of us completely become numb or suspicious. 
we mistrust,  be suspicious or even get aggressive towards the slightest positive thing in the world. we question the intent of the people we already know and love which tears us from inside out. 
the flashes of the incident keeps on coming through, compelling us to think of every opportunity we had to escape the wrong. we know we were helpless but cannot accept the fact and put ourselves to blame. a guilt of not being capable enough to save ourselves hovers our mind creating deep incurable wounds. 
but now no more. 
let's speak up and above all realise and accept the fact that it was not our mistake. #meetoomovement #metoo #hearttalk  #womanhood #woman #safety #india #life #lifequotes #quotes #writerscommunity #poetsofinstagram #tales #kanpur #lucknow #pune #agra #hyderabad #chennai  #delhi #hearttalk #digyourstory

text_retweet:
#repost @sacredsons
・・・
we live in a society divorced from the sacred - where boys are so often forced to grow up without healthy examples of masculinity and rather than being initiated into manhood through meaningful rites of passage, we get pseudo initiations like binge drinking, drug abuse, and blind sexual conquest which doesn't serve our growth.

how can we expect men to be present and loving partners and fathers when we're shamed into stifling our emotions as boys, and never see men who are emotionally available being celebrated? to add insult to injury we are bombarded with examples of men from tv, movies, sports and music who are psychologically immature and often misogynistic.

what else could we expect other than the me too movement? and we all know that we need to make some huge changes and evolve our collective perspective if we want to prevent #metoo2

as sacred sons who are honoring our purpose we are doing just that. we are rising to demonstrate by example how men have a responsibility to do the inner work to heal our wounds, so that we may protect and provide for our families from a place of love, not obligation. and to show up in our communities as leaders demonstrating healthy, generative masculinity.

we are grateful for the 70 men who traveled from arizona, throughout california, colorado, florida, hawaii, nevada, georgia, oklahoma, texas, washington, new york, mexico and the uk to join us at @libertyarising this past weekend to challenge their growth edges, break through into greater freedom, and embody sacred masculinity so that we show up in the world as fathers, husbands, uncles, brothers, lovers, and sons who honor our sacred purpose as leaders in this movement to shift this paradigm and redefine masculinity.

thank you to all of you men and to all the women and children beside us who inspire us to no end. there is so much we can say but for now we feel that these words from our brother @trevorspring who facilitated an incredible workshop 'wild & wise' sums it up well... . "the calm after the storm. walking and flying away from the first @sacredsons gathering today. ✌🏽 these stones. these men. this heart. so much grounded love.

text:
ta plats! kampen mot patriarkatet har tagit oss ända hit och nu får vi inte stanna. ett år sedan #metoo exploderade. marken var jämnad av hundratals års kamp för allas lika värde och rättigheter. dammluckan öppnades och inget blir sig likt igen. 💪
ta plats! även när det inte känns bra. för när du kliver utanför det utrymme som patriarkatet tilldelat dig, kommer du att få en pisksnärt. det är oundvikligt och det händer alla utom normbärare. du kommer att ångra dig, skämmas, önska det ogjort. inget är ju enklare än att stanna i den avsedda zonen. 💪
ta plats! det kan kännas som om pisksnärten tvingar oss tillbaka till ursprungsläget, men så är det inte. för varje litet steg vi tar, flyttas positionerna framåt. inte bara för oss själva utan även för alla andra som befinner sig i underordning. varje steg utanför normen påverkar normen pyttepyttelite, oftast så lite att vi inte ser det. men tillsammans med alla andra pyttepyttesmå steg kommer det till slut att bli för mycket och patriarkatet kommer att falla. 💪
ta plats! för att du är värd det men också för alla andra som också befinner sig i underordning! ta klivet, ta plats och ta betalt! och sen, när det gör ont, hjälps vi åt och tröstar, säger att det onda går över, du gjorde nåt bra, heja dig!
💪

text:
actress sonakshi sinha is not ready to comment on the tanushree dutta-nana patekar row, saying it is important to know both sides of the story before commenting. “it is better to say the least about this issue because there will always be two sides to the story. we have often seen that when someone comes up with such an issue, then the media and people start discussing about it. but later we find out that the truth is something else. so, i think without knowing both sides of the stories, we shouldn’t get into it,” sonakshi said when asked about her stand on the issue at an event in mumbai.

the #metoo movement has gained momentum in bollywood with tanushree alleging that nana harassed her on the sets of their 2008 film horn ok pleassss. tanushree has also filed a police complaint against nana, who has denied the allegations.

sonakshi said that creating a safer workplace for all was a must. “if a woman feels unsafe in a working environment, then i think it is anyway very wrong. no woman should be made to feel unsafe when she goes to work and strict measures should be taken to make sure that a woman is safe wherever she goes.” sonakshi said that she hasn’t experienced sexual harassment in her life but feels girls must be taught self-defense. “i would urge our government to incorporate self-defense as a compulsory subject. i have been saying this for a long time. “if a girl knows how to protect herself from a very young age, then i think she can protect herself. she need not be dependent on a man.” #sonakshi, #sonakshisinha, #nanapatekar, #tanushreedutta, #aslisona

text:
fair apparel. was a sector within fair market. that included t-shirts designed by women artists and designers that respond to this particular socio-political moment. the t-shirts were included as works of art in and of themselves or as artifacts of social and art historical movements that deepen our understanding of feminism and contemporary creative art movements.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
artists included were otherwild x herstory with the future is female t-shirt, zoila darton-word agency with creator shirt, bella doña, tatyana fazlalizadeh, and guerrilla girls.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo: diana larrea / @parcialmentenublada

text:
#exactly #vote — #donaldtrumpjr.'s new girlfriend, kimberly guilfoyle, is leaving her role at fox news. the network said in a statement that it "has parted ways with kimberly guilfoyle," and cnn reports that she will join trump jr. on the campaign trail for the 2018 midterm elections. here's what you should know about her.
-
donald trump jr.'s girlfriend kimberly guilfoyle calls them the 'perfect team'
-
donald trump jr. and former fox news personality kimberly guilfoyle have been dating since the spring, and things are still going strong between them as the summer draws to a close and the midterms fast approach.
-
speaking to page six's richard johnson at a hamptons fundraiser, guilfoyle gushed about her whirlwind romance with the first son.
-
"i've never been happier," guilfoyle reportedly said. "i am thrilled to be joining don jr. across the country in amplifying the america-first message. we are working non-stop and we make the perfect team."
-
during the bridgehampton event, sources say that the couple "arrived like royalty and worked the room together," added that they appeared to be "a real power couple."
-
and, after guilfoyle introduced her boyfriend to the stage, don jr. called his ladylove "a tough act to follow."
-
the unlikely pair was first linked back in may, two months after he split from ex vanessa trump.
-
later in june, the couple made their rumored romance instagram official after sharing a slew of airbrushed photos from their weekend fishing trip to montana.
-
he calls her "junior mint," while she refers to her man as "pooh bear."
-
trump jr. once asserted on a radio show in 2013, that women who can't handle workplace harassment should teach kindergarten.

text:
it has been just over a year since the first allegations made against harvey weinstein brought the #metoo movement into the media’s attention. what has changed during this year?
🔸
the good thing is, something that has started as yet another thing happening far away in the glamour of hollywood has since become much bigger than that. stories started by #metoo have become a prominent part of the information landscape, and a lot of the society was forced to be engaged in this conversation.
🔸
however, the current culture existed for a long time, so it was only to be expected that eventually there will be forces fighting the change. what evidence do i have for that? i list some of the things that i see being used as responses to the #metoo stories.
🔸
the myth of the perfect victim (and a perfect activist), whereby a woman speaking out is measured against an impossible standard of perfection in her behaviour and emotional response. any deviations from perfection are used to justify what was done to her. the truth is, there are no perfect victims. we are all flawed human beings. and make no mistake, when a “perfect” victim comes along, she is not believed, either: dr blasey ford, a white, non-immigrant, educated, from a middle class family, wife and mother, blond and skinny and conservatively dressed, without any known skeletons in the closet, was made to testify on national tv. and then her testimony was ignored.
🔸
a backlash suggesting that this is all too much. because #metoo stories are in the news often and the subject is quite unsavoury, a perception has been created that a great many men have borne the consequences of their part behaviour and that false accusations are wide-spread. the statistics shows this is simply not the case.
🔸
the “everyone deserves a second chance” fallacy, used in respect of popular, rich, talented men, who have given no apologies and shown no evidence of any work on themselves to deserve such a chance.
⬇️⬇️⬇️

text:
today a year ago.
civil rights activist tarana burke from the bronx, ny, founded the #metoo movement in 2006 that spread through a tweet by alyssa milano and shook the world with a clear message:
✖️
millions and millions of women all over the world have since the beginning of time been exposed to sexual harassment, violence, assault, violation and abuse. every day. every hour. every minute. in all parts of society.
✖️
a culture of silence has been broken and we will never never never ever give up.
✖️
this is a global movement for human rights. don’t make it out to be anything else.
✖️
don’t ever be silent- allow your voice to be heard. ✖️
whatever we wear, wherever we go
yes means yes, and no means no!
✖️
this revolution is not over until we get to where we need to be. it will continue everywhere, all the time.
✖️
be brave. speak up. remember that you are not alone.
✖️
there are millions of women who’s got your back and we won’t let go.
✖️
wake up every morning and be proud to continue our united fight to crush the patriarchy!👊🏿👊🏾👊🏽👊🏼👊🏻
✖️
#metoo #metaltoo #taranaburke #alyssamilano #timesup #speakup #nevergiveup #bebrave

text:
#metoo | part i
exactly one year ago, this hashtag went viral; it was the beginning of a revolution. @milano_alyssa suggested that women should reply with "me too" to her tweet if they've been sexually harassed or assaulted. 
i fought long with myself - i wanted to be able to talk about this topic so badly last year, but i didn't. i couldn't back then; i wasn't ready to speak up. after all, my "me too moments" were one of the main reasons for my eating disorder (because it's about regaining control). now, i know about the healing power of openness and i feel way stronger since. also, it's important to share our stories to see that we are not alone in this. i'm nervous, but it's time for me to say: me too.
i could probably write a whole book about sexual harassment; it's somehow part of being a woman - and that's more than sad. i received disgusting comments on the street and online. i found my pictures between pornographic content only because i wore leather - and what people commented is nothing a woman wants to read. there are still pictures i can't remove until today.
but not only that. i know what it feels like when boundaries are crossed, when several noes are ignored; i know what unsolicited touches are; about the uncomfortable feeling you get and how the body freezes. i know what it feels like to be pushed, pressured and manipulated. i know about abusive situations, about feeling helpless and weak. and it's not what most think - no strangers, no drugs, no alcohol etc. those people i'm talking about, are "normal" guys. it could probably be your friend or the shy guy who's always super polite. most guys aren't even aware that they are toxic - because guys are still taught that women only play hard to get and that they have to push them a little until the girl gives in and they get what they want. if i say no, don't try to convince me; i have my reasons. only an emphatic, freely given yes, means yes. consent isn't a grey zone; it's strictly black and white. the only things that turns grey is the life of the person that gets assaulted. i accepted apologies i never received to move on; i have flash backs and memories i don’t want to have…

text: ich habe jetzt zwei wochen gebraucht, um mich zu fassen und dieses buch zu kommentieren. louise o’neill hat ein grandioses buch geschrieben. vorab möchte ich sagen, dass dieses buch nichts für schwache nerven ist, weil es ein problem thematisiert das in unserer gesellschaft leider ausgeblendet wird. nach einem jahr #metoo hat sich zwar viel verändert, doch vergewaltigung wie in diesem buch finden immer noch statt. überlebende werden immer noch mit gesellschaftlicher verachtung konfrontiert. ich habe schon vorher meine solidarität mit den männern und frauen, die solche gräueltaten erleben mussten bekannt und setzte mich weiterhin für sie ein. das gelungene in diesem buch, ist die tatsache, dass die protagonistin nicht sympathisch ist. es zeigt, dass es jedem/r passieren kann und leute von denen niemals so etwas gerechnet hat, können zu monstern werden. dieses buch ist nicht perfekt, die geschichte endet nicht gut, aber das macht sie umso realistischer  insgesamt konfrontiert sie uns mit der wahrheit auch weißt sie eine riesige ungerechtigkeit auf, die bekämpft werden muss. egal  wer du bist , eine solche ungerechtigkeit darfst du nicht ignorieren. mach die augen auf, lies dieses buch oder informiere dich anderweitig. niemand möchte, dass einem das selbst passiert. also lasst uns gemeinsam dazu beitragen, dass das niemandem mehr passiert. bleibt aufmerksam! #rapeculture #victimblaming #ok2share #redmylips #slutshaming #metoo #injustice #books #reading

text: 💗 | shot by @strangebirdproductions for @metoomvmt • extremely humbled to be a part of this campaign. as an artist, change-maker & a survivor of sexual assault, i recognize that it’s important and necessary that i utilize my platform to share information/knowledge regarding social issues, especially those that affect the communities i am a part of. be it the black community, the lgbtqia+ community, the femme/womxn community, it’s important that we take time to educate both the masses & ourselves. there is always more to learn. allow yourself to be checked, allow others the space to be heard, allow yourself space to expand your perspective & knowingness. we have so much knowledge amongst the collective. it’s about time we center our focus on the state of the collective, and bring the silenced voices of sexual assault survivors (men, womxn, trans, femme, non-binary folx alike) to the forefront. • i’m rambling lol, so i’ll leave y’all with this. you matter. your story matters. our collective voices are being heard. despite what them old, headass yt men be shouting (and trust, i know they be maaaaadddd loud w/ their opinions), know that your truth overpowers all the ignorance/lack of empathy they spew our way. remember your power, harness that shit & show up for each other. appreciative of all that @taranajaneen + this movement stand for, thank you again. #metoo

text:
we live in a society divorced from the sacred - where boys are so often forced to grow up without healthy examples of masculinity, and rather than being initiated into manhood through meaningful rites of passage, we get pseudo initiations like binge drinking, drug abuse, and blind sexual conquest, neither of which help us become men.

how can we expect men to be present, loving partners and fathers when we're shamed into stifling our emotions as boys, and never shown what an emotionally available man even looks like? to add insult to injury we are bombarded with examples of men from tv, movies, sports and music who are psychologically immature and often misogynistic. .

what else could we expect other than the me too movement? and now we all know that we need to make some huge changes and evolve our collective perspective if we want to prevent #metoo2 .

as sacred sons who are honoring our purpose we are doing just that. we are rising to demonstrate by example how men have a responsibility to do the inner work to heal our wounds, so that we may protect and provide for our families from a place of love, not obligation. and to show up in our communities as leaders expressing healthy, generative masculinity. .

we are grateful for the 70 men who traveled from arizona, throughout california, colorado, florida, hawaii, nevada, georgia, oklahoma, texas, washington, new york, mexico and the uk to join us at @libertyarising this past weekend to challenge their growth edges, break through into greater freedom, and embody sacred masculinity so that we show up in the world as fathers, husbands, uncles, brothers, lovers, and sons who honor our sacred purpose as leaders in this movement to shift this paradigm and redefine masculinity. .

thank you to all of you men and to all the women and children beside us who inspire us to no end. there is so much we can say but for now we feel that these words from our brother @wild_and_wise who facilitated an incredible workshop 'wild & wise' sums it up well... . "the calm after the storm. walking and flying away from the first @sacredsons gathering today. ✌🏽 these stones. these men. this heart. so much grounded love... 👇🏿👇🏽👇
name: MASCULINE ALCHEMY + EMBODIMENT

text:
tro det eller ej, men idag ska jag för första gången skriva om något viktigt här. kul men framförallt roligt, visst? :) den 15 oktober 2017, för precis ett år sedan, föddes revolutionen #metoo. det blev startskottet för en ny kvinnorörelse med internet som högkvarter.

ni vet känslan när man skriver ett nervöst sms & riskerar att få dissen? så kändes det för mig innan jag vågade lägga ut #metoo på min instastory. efteråt vällde dock en våg av stolthet över mig med all sin kraft. jag är stolt över att vara en del av #metoo. inte för att jag varit med om det värsta tänkbara & äntligen, efter år av tystnad & skam, känner tillräckligt med stöd för att våga berätta. utan snarare för att jag kommer kunna berätta till min framtida dotter att #metoo bidrog till förändring. och att jag var en av alla kvinnor som satte ner foten i ett högt & dånande "nu får det banne mig att vara nog". tack vare denna simpla hashtag kommer hon inte behöva skrika för att bli hörd. hennes kropp kommer vara hennes & ingen annans, oavsett vad. och hennes trygghet kommer vara en självklarhet, inte något som när som helst kan tas ifrån henne. 
må därför #metoo's efterskalv föralltid eka på varje arbetsplats, dansgolv, skola, torg och i alla omklädningsrum, hem, städer & länder.

tarana burke & alyssa milano, tack för att ni bad oss göra våra röster hörda. 19 miljoner kvinnor svarade på er vädjan om förändring. vi grep tag i varandras händer & sa alla med samma  frustration "me too". sedan den dagen släpper vi inte varandras händer, än mindre håller vi käften någonsin igen. <33

text:
meet me monday
10•15•18
camilla sanchez is a 61 year old women who graduated from cedar bluff high school. while attending, females were let into the ffa. but, it was common for some schools to still not let girls into the ag classes. experiencing this first hand, we thought cam would have some ideas on the subject.
the interview:
q: none of the girls were allowed even into the classroom, correct?
a: true.
q: would you guys fight to be in the classes?
a: of course. especially me, i was the tomboy that wanted everything to do with #metoo movements. it was our time for girls to be involved with that.
••
comments & additions:
cam says even the boys thought it wasn’t fair. they were allowed in the “fha” or in the home economic classes, and they told their teachers that. she says they would come in and eat all the food, and when their pants broke open i was the one to fix them, being the best seamstress in the class. (cam is also excited about @b_b_hill , our schools first female ag advisor😉)

text: i have lots of favorite quotes. lots! but this one always comes to mind. this quote reminds me of strong women, falsely accused women, women whom many tried to destroy... it reminds me of #halfhangedmary - a woman they tried to hang because a man's sickness was blamed on her, but the next morning they went out to find her still alive. in their minds, this confirmed her witch status, but she lived out the rest of her life left alone. this quote speaks to me and reminds me that i'm strong and i come from a lineage of #strongwomen. share your #favoritequote and why with myself, @5rfarmoregon and @smallfarmcharm for our #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth photo challenge. use hashtag #thecluckerbehindthecoop. what quote lifts you up? if you're like me, for too many years i left hurtful words control me. #nomore

text: i was 4, i believe, when a man broke into my home. my baby sitter let him. my sister was 3. i’m glad nothing happened to her. my mom had to take me to the doctor. nobody has found him. my baby sitter sits free. #metoo it really doesn’t matter what you wear or how old you are. the fact it has happened and the fact it continues to happen is sickening. and everyone who is “scared” to be falsely accused, imagine crying to your mom about being scared for your life when you’re walking by yourself after dark, always having to keep an eye on your drink at the bar, scared to even say no because everything now means yes, or afraid that when you’re going on a run, it could be the last time the public eye sees you. if you’re scared of the #metoo movement, maybe there is a reason behind it

text:
tw and long post warning ⚠️ this is a post i’ve been meaning to do for a while so here goes - in london there is an incredible group of women trying to raise awareness and initiate an open conversation about sexual abuse and violence. the project is called @100womeniknow and as well as trying to create a platform for people to voice their experiences, they also run workshops on consent to help eradicate rape culture, and educate people on the insidious nature of sexual abuse. 
this book is a culmination of the stories that started the project. it’s not an easy read but that’s because this isn’t an easy subject. you’ll find no filtered photos on this post because this book is unashamedly unfiltered. 
100womeniknow is a charity that means a lot to me for numerous reasons, not least because realising that almost every woman you know has a story like this is deeply concerning and upsetting. they’ve also helped me to open up about my own experiences and for that i am forever grateful. 
this book has made me cry and broken my heart with every page turn, but it was also one of the most liberating books i’ve ever read. 
if you feel able to, please consider purchasing a copy and reading the stories it tells. profits from the book go to help fund the workshops 100womeniknow provide. 
you can read more about this amazing charity on their website: www.100womeniknow.com/ 
#100womeniknow #consent #sexeducation #london #women #timesup #metoo

text:
“you determine your #worth, not them.” coming out of #domesticviolence and #abuse is like being born again. you have to reassess every bit of your thinking and unlearn everything that #manipulative #lair told you about yourself. you have to take back control not only #physically but also #mentally and #psychologically and in some cases, it feels like you’re starting over. the more you see how their actions (not yours) affected you mentally and in your view of yourself, you can start to heal. you can start to see your true worth. their actions show how they don’t value you, but it doesn’t change your true value.

text:
som de flesta vet, startades #metoo av tarana burke 2006.
för ca 1 år sedan slogs världen med storm av denna hashtagg då bland annat alyssa milano uppmärksammat/ blivit något slags outnämnt nytt ansikte utåt för taggen.
sen dess har vi sett backpack taggar på #metoo som ska lyfta olika saker i relevant eller icke-relevant anda (#mentoo #miautoo för att ge två exempel)
att män som blir utsatta för sexuella övergrepp skall få tala ut håller jag med om, men att förövare skall få sitta och tycka synd om sig i en tagg känns mindre kul.
att de sedan ska göras taggar för  utsatta katter (ex misskötsel, övergivna osv) i en metoo anda, känns också rätt.. tradigt.
absolut jättebra att vilja och försöka uppmärksamma katter (och djur) i utsatthet men man kan väl finurla ut något lite mer eget än att rida på kvinnors utsatthet? sen tycker jag att tarana behöver få extremt mycket mer uppmärksamhet för sitt arbete bakom metoo, och att poc icke-män skulle få synas och höras mer i dessa vita delar av världen. kan direkt säga att många tycker om att kontra den sista meningen med "men så många anonyma historier vet du ju inte om insändaren är vit eller poc" vilket är sant men om vi kollar rent statistiskt så är majoriteten av de som synts vita.
vad anser ni själva?
dags att släppa #metoo och låta andra ämnen rida på den ryggen, eller bör de olika taggstartarna och aktivisterna hitta egna namn och taggar?

#metoo #intedinfetisch

text:
för ett år sedan gick jag med nycklarna i handen och knöt nävar i frustration. för ett år sedan hade jag inte sagt så mycket om en kollega petade på mig, sådär i förbifarten och baraföratt, sådär som folk [män] gör för att få uppmärksamhet, visa prov på sin humor och sin makt. idag sa jag nej. ett klart och tydligt och tämligen aggressivt #nej när en kollega petade på mig. en kollega som jag tillrättavisat vid ett flertal tillfällen under det gångna året. en kollega som bett om ursäkt och som dragit så kallade me too-skämt och som bett om ursäkt igen osv. jag blir förbannad och förbannat trött. på såna som han. på såna [män] som ser sig som helylle. på såna utan självinsikt. för världen är full av såna. så, för att motverka min trötthet - och för att patriarkatet inte krossar sig på egen hand - virkar jag numera knogjärn av garnrester. och går med nycklarna i handen. .
#metoo #allamän #knogjärn #virkat #handarbete #feminist #feminism #femfair .
det är förövrigt ett medvetet val från min sida att endast fokusera på en vardaglig incident. dels för att jag saknar ork för att beröra brutalare händelser, dels för att jag anser att tillsynes oskyldiga övertramp också förtjänar uppmärksamhet.

#grandiosityevents in partnership with the #attorneys #poker #tournament #celebrity #charity #benefit for protectourdefenders.com saturday february 23rd 2019 #mgm #nationalharbor 
to date, pod has supported over 800 service members, veterans, and their families with over $8million in free legal services. in the past, pod has supported an average of 200 people a year. in 2018 alone, due to the attention of the #metoo movement, pod will surpass 500 people—at least doubling our normal support levels. time is critical as we require more sustained resources to meet the needs of those who come to us at ever increasing levels.

your priority needs to be ✨loving yourself✨ then you allow that love and inner joy to flow to those around you.
you cannot pour from an empty cup.💕

the @aasas_ab #ibelieveyou campaign is at @ualberta this week sharing messages of hope and encouragement. whether you’ve disclosed to someone close to you, aren’t sure of what to do after something happened to you, or you want to know what to do next, i believe you. take your time, heal how you need to heal, feel what you’re feeling, and use the resources available to you when you’re ready. i wish i would have known how to approach my own experiences of assault throughout my life. it’s so much to wade through on your own. find your supports, be brave, and take care of yourself. it’s not your fault and you’re going to be okay. 🖤

text: along with dance, i've also been able to find myself through poetry. whatever i'm feeling, whether it be happy or sad or anxious or confused, poetry has allowed me to gather my thoughts and understand what's going on and that has allowed me to better deal with whatever is going on for myself at that moment. i wrote this poem after being told by many of my friends that my assault didn't happen. so many women have come out since then, and still so many of them are told it was their fault or it didn't really happen. if we are telling survivors of abuse and assault that their stories are invalid, we are telling assailants that their actions are okay. it's time for survivors to not only be listened to, but to be heard. i hope all of you catch the "disease called reality," because this world could use more people with honest eyes and open minds #believesurvivors #metoo

⁣

⁣

text:
i have some feelings today, you guys!! this might be a long one. can we all get on board with the idea that feelings are real and valid? that the response to feelings should never be “it’s not a big deal” or my favorite “calm down!” just no. if someone is upset or scared those feelings matter way more than whatever your intentions might have been. let’s start there. we can do better. .
this applies to men and women. this applies to adults and children. this applies to white people and everyone else. this applies everywhere. .
.
.
.

10/13/2018 - ironman world championships -kailua kona, hawaii, for completion of my 3rd ironman in 6 months.
.

to be honest, i think that this sport saved my life a few years ago. since then this sport has bent me, broke me, rebuilt and shaped me. today it is reminder to show up for myself, to be gritty, and how if something bad happens, it’s not the end. #graceandgrit .
.
.
.

text_retweet:
3 days ago, when i searched kalavantin fort on google, the results were scary and showing it as one of most dangerous trek.

but somehow i overcame my fear and went for trekking.

here it goes:
on day 1, met some strangers and did night trekking for 2-3 hrs to reach the base village 'thakurwadi'.
after reaching there, we took locally prepared tasty food.
now the time was for camping. our camps were at perfect place under the sky full of stars with bonfire and view of city full of lights. we sat there, enjoyed the beauty and discussed ramdom #metoo #bollywoodmovies, jobs, astrology, personal life, johnysingham, played antakshri n blah blah. 
on 2nd day, we started trekking for the fort at 5:00am & reached there before sunrise.
although no one wanted to come back to attend daily offices, but we had to come back, so return journey started.
अगली trip के लिए पैसे भी चाहिए ना।
trek was easy with little steepness at some points only.

had breakfast as poha n chai with some local 🍋 grass flavour at base village.  descending for next 2 hrs.

outcome of trip-
overcame fear, 3rd trek in list, convert strangers into friends, checked my singing ability which disappointed many, johny singham fan, keep your stuff with you always, found a tour guide who is a true own story teller -jhoot bol ke

thanks @smallstepsadventures .
.
.
.
. .
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: för ett år sedan påbörjades det en revolution. en strid, en kamp, ett motstånd där tystade röster plötsligt blåste upp en storm. det slutade med att våldtäktsmännen flög som löv i varje litet hörn. plötsligt såg man både offren och våldsamma män. alla dessa våldtäktsmän som annars har funnits överallt trots att ingen tycks ha känt någon. skillnaden mellan alla andra gånger och just denna gång var att det blev rättegångar. det blev straff. det blev avsked. det blev förändring. vi kvinnor förändrade. tillsammans mot ett patriarkat som annars skadar oss, objektifierar oss och bokstavligt talat dödar oss. min kropp ska ingen röra utan tillåtelse. min hud ska varken känna kalla, främmande, händer på stan, på hemmafesten, på krogen eller på festivalen. aldrig ska min kropp behöva utsättas och aldrig ska min kropp behöva bli obejktifierad. aldrig ska mitt nej nekas. aldrig ska jag ens behöva fundera på hur kort min kjol är. våra kvinnokroppar ska hyllas, prisas och framförallt respekteras. vi måste bara komma ihåg att "me too" fortfarande är exakt lika viktigt idag så som det var för ett år sedan. att inte lägga problemen på is. att inte låta oss stå där med våra öppna hjärtan och sedan glömmas bort tillsammans med tidens gång. det händer fortfarande. jag är fortfarande rädd. jag är fortfarande otrygg. jag är fortfarande en del av den grupp som behöver få höras ännu mer. och nej, jag är inte en trångsynt, previligerad man. jag är en stark och betydelsefull kvinna. låt oss skrika. låt oss höras. och på riktigt, ta oss på allvar. #metoo #feminism #grlpwr

text:
#스쿨미투 #metoo #withyou
-
불쾌하고 잘못되었다는 것을 우리 모두가 알면서도 아무도 입 밖으로 내지 않았다. 너무나도 만연한 행위라 잘못된 줄 몰랐다. 그때는 고등학교가 입시가 대학이 뭐그리 중요했을까. 왜 그리도 우리가 잘못했다고 생각했을까.
그때 누군가 그건 잘못된 거라고 그들이 이상한거라고 말해줬다면 함께 소리를 낼 수 있었다면, 용기를 낼 수 있었을까.
-
우리는 서로의 용기다.
-
[참여방법]
1. #스쿨미투 #metoo # with you 해시태그와 함께 자신의 연대문을 작성한다.
2. 인증사진을 찍고 게시한다.
3. 최소 3명이상을 태그한다.
4. 태그를 받은 사람은 참여한다.
-

text:
on july 5, #donaldtrump had previously offered to give #elizabethwarren — whom he calls “pocahontas — $1 million that she could provide to any charity if she took a dna test to show that she has native american ancestry.
.
“let’s say i’m debating #pocahontas,” he said at a rally. “i promise you i’ll do this: i will take, you know those little kits they sell on television... learn your heritage!”.
.
“and in the middle of the debate, when she proclaims that she is of indian heritage because her mother said she has high cheek bones, that is her only evidence, her mother said we have high cheek bones,” trump continued.
.
“we will take that little kit -- but we have to do it gently. because we’re in the #metoo generation, we have to do it gently,” he said. “and we will very gently take that kit, and slowly toss it, hoping it doesn’t injure her arm, and we will say: i will give you a million dollars to your favorite charity, paid for by trump, if you take the test and it shows you’re an indian.”.
.

.
there are no words 
that will justify your pain.
my world had him.
that was my biggest mistake.
shower of love, horror of being naive.
starting to fall, feeling so tall
will you still attack me
when you have realised
i wanted to be free 
of what they created against a solitude soul
which never drove to grave near by,
but you killed it with your so called pure world
and words
i'm not sure if its me or your deed.
falling was the guilt to be preach
or you trying places to reach.

i have felt alone till now
were my words, no new. 
in return you holded my hand and said
i'll there for you
and it is beautiful thing,how?

things have changed and are changing
no one is left here 
to listen your stories to say wow.
we shared a mighty weapon earlier.
which will now destroy you.
pen, penning down what you did,
your deeds,
now open your pleasing but repulsive eyes
pay your heed.
we have aroused, not only against you.
but against every weed like you.
show your face, and see ours
one holding eyes to every new pretty
and another holding tears against things 
it has faced nasty.
i don't know where to stop this now.
cause you also didn't.
- parth kashyap

text:
side note: when you're out alone in the middle of nowhere with no network, just nod and ignore. -- someone told me just yesterday, "with all this me too happening, boys will be afraid of being boys." i didn't realize guys were just animalistic horrors incapable of seeing women as different beings deserving of respect.

but for those men so troubled by the movement, that must be so tough - being afraid of being yourself.

#metoo isn't just for the women out there. it's for the victims. for that little child who didn't understand that she had been molested. for the woman who said no and was ignored. for the man who is grappling with being a survivor. 
for the person who doesn't even understand what assault means.

it's for a world that deserves better.

text:
#rapecultureisreal // @stephanieawmartin 
full text below. 
don’t tell me what i’ve experienced isn’t real, as if some leftist rogue theory is trying to topple white male patriarchy. realization that you have all the power, the confidence to defend actions once wrought upon me, and still daily consumes, is all but a figment of some conspiracy in the minds of loons, disbelieving the moment his cock took my consent. does that make you squirm? was it too graphic a depiction of the scene which replays, daily, on my skin in memory of moments he stole? rape is real, the culture supporting such heinous action stands stalwart, a wall you intend to not let fall, perhaps due to you not wanting the world to see a monster underneath the layers of macho bravado. do you sicken at the power play as it splays, providing women a place to stand and raise their voice? laugh all you want, you are nothing more than a discontent soul, wishing for anger, hoping to spread hate.

text: idag har det visst gått 1 år sen #metoo exploderade över internet och sociala medier. min reaktion när jag såg det första gången var oj. i princip alla kvinnor jag känner har vid något eller flera tillfällen blivit psykist eller fysiskt illa behandlade av en man. vi har alla olika ont av det. men vad säger det egentligen om samhället att vi inte har ont av det ibland? att allt är så normaliserat att man inte ens tänker på att man blir trakasserad och förnedrad. man skrattar lite. haha. det var ju lite galet. jaja. men det sjukaste av allt som hände var att se hur män reagerade. dom blev upprörda. men inte för att kvinnor runt omkring dom blivit illa behandlade, utan för att det fick dom att känna sig obekväma och påhoppade. "det är inte rimligt". nä, det är verkligen inte rimligt att det är såhär. men det betyder inte att det inte är så. "det är ju en bra grej, men det är ju överdrivet när alla skriver me too". så istället för att bli förbannad och ledsen över att i stort sett alla kvinnor känner igen sig i att de blivit illa behandlade, så misstror man dom för att det känns för mycket? som att det är lögn? vad tjänar man exakt på att ljuga om något sånt här? jag kan bara inte förstå. "alla kan ju inte ha blivit våldtagna och är det inte våldtäkt så räknas det inte". så du menar då alltså att det är helt okej för någon okänd person att ta på mig? att slå till mig på rumpan? att grabba tag i mig och göra vad den känner för - sålänge det inte är våldtäkt? det tycker inte jag. och nej, alla kvinnor i världen har inte blivit våldtagna, men jag överdriver inte när jag säger att 99% har med all säkerhet fått en klapp på rumpan eller en hand på bröstet eller sexuella ord ropade efter sig. det är sant. och bara för att det är svårt att förstå varför så många ska behöva uppleva detta så betyder det inte att det inte händer. varje jäkla dag. i hela världen. och man vet inte bättre alltid heller. man får lära sig att det får man räkna med. går du ut på krogen så kommer du få händer där du inte vill ha dom av främlingar, bara för att du är där och är tjej. det ska inte behöva vara såhär. män! bli inte kränkta och misstro oss - hjälp till att ställa till rätta istället.

text: there are truths that must be addressed and understood by all sides b4 we can have any type of forward progress as a body of one (humanity). accountability, responsibility, and genuine open discourse about the facts of white privilege and what it truly means to be black in amerikkka is necessary... even tho i agree with the principle, kanye is ass backwards with that whole "try love first campaign". we have been so tortured, so battered, so mistreated, so traumatized, so damaged by our experience as melanated people in this country, that we have internalized those experiences and now conflict that same damage on ourselves without an opposing force in sight. soo b4 we jump out the window to love others we gotta relearn what it is to truly love our selves again and no longer crying victim, but taking our destiny and fate as a ppl back into our hands! instead of going out of his way to "love" a misogynistic, ego driven, racist asshole. kanye should be going out of his way to hug those kids killing each other at a alarming rate from his very own hometown of chicago!! and just as it applies to the individual, "you cannot properly love someone else until you learn how to truly love yourself", it applies to us as a body of people.. so i am sorry kanye, b4 i can learn to love and understand a "leader" who shows no remorse for the plight of my people, it is of utmost importance that i learn to love my self first and foremost!#wearenotvictims #wearegreatness #selflove #randomthoughtsonabetterlife #thisisamerica #thisisus #blackexcellence #racism #whiteprivilege #flawedsystem #blacklivesmatter #blacklove #maga #alllivesmatter #metoo #society #reality #culture #truth #understanding #properdiscourse #differences #whitepower #blackpower #illusions #deception #divideandconquer #powerofthepeople ✊🏿✊🏾✊🏽✊🏻✊

text:
fair apparel. was a sector within fair market. that included t-shirts designed by women artists and designers that respond to this particular socio-political moment. the t-shirts were included as works of art in and of themselves or as artifacts of social and art historical movements that deepen our understanding of feminism and contemporary creative art movements.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
artists included were otherwild x herstory with the future is female t-shirt, zoila darton-word agency with creator shirt, bella doña, tatyana fazlalizadeh, and guerrilla girls.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.

for this, we need your support. 
we request you to sign this petition and help us reach the highest authorities.
find the link to this petition in our bio. #metoo #timeisup

text:
ett år har nu gått sedan #metoo.
▪️
expressen har träffat fem kvinnor som var – eller fortfarande är – i uppropets mitt. hur ser de på rörelsen i dag? har sverige förändrats av #metoo? och: vad händer nu?
▪️
alexandra pascalidou:
– jag har träffat många män och unga killar som tydligt tar ställning mot sexism, sexuella övergrepp och allmänt sunkig människosyn och som vill engagera sig. nu är det dags för männen att ta över den här stafettpinnen.
▪️
anja pärson:
– ända ner på dagisnivå hör man kommentarer om att tjejer inte kan. där behöver man sätta ner foten och säga: ”hörrni grabbar, vet ni vad – alla kan, alla är lika”. man ska kunna våga, oavsett om man är tjej eller kille. kan metoo-kampanjen driva vidare alla de här frågorna så är det fantastiskt.
▪️
alice bah kuhnke:
– jag tror att det finns en risk att vi som är chefer och ledare känner att det är gjort och klart. det riskerar att bli det stora bakslaget. därför har jag bestämt mig för att vara som en grävling och hålla fast vid den här frågan.
▪️
cissi wallin:
– jag har gott hopp om den nya generationens män, men från de i min ålder har det tyvärr varit ljummet. det är deppigt, men de har inte den erfarenheten av sexuellt förtryck eller övergrepp. det är dags att sätta sig in i det och börja förstå.
▪️
gunilla axén:
– tiden efter #metoo för mig har varit en kamp mellan dåtid och nutid. en ganska tuff kamp.
▪️
läs alla fem reportagen på expressen.se. ett av dem finns länkat i vår profil.

text:
there is light at the end of the tunnel.
research by the fawcett society has identified there has been a shift in attitudes to sexual harassment following the #metoo movement. their findings, supported by law firm hogan lovells, revealed 53% said that understanding of what is seen as acceptable behaviour has changed. further, over half of young people (aged 18-34) said they are more likely to speak up against sexual harassment, including 58% of young men.
while this indicates a change in attitude, does it motivate a change in behaviour?
both slater and gordon and the fawcett society have called on the government to introduce policies to tackle workplace harassment. but is this the most effective way to eradicate the issue? collectively, we need to be proactive in bringing about real change – understanding what motivates this behaviour, being committed to cultivating a culture of openness and respect, and giving employees the tools and confidence to speak out.

text:
post by @artandananta_ -  today i itch to say #metoo and rip you inside out. it is an opportunity, a great opportunity for that matter. of course i’ve told the world about your filth and torments before, and i will keep telling the world ever after. but i know that today when i talk about you, there will be eyebrows raised and fingers pointed. when, for the last two years you put the blame on me and mocked my tears, and tricked everybody around us into thinking how a godly soul you are and how i must feel privileged to have you, the time has come when everybody’d know what happens behind closed doors. everybody’d know who is the saint and who is the demon.
i spoke to a friend about this decision to spill out the milk. he encouraged me, and why not. if one person has the right to stab you over and over again and tell the world they’re actually loving you and their family pushing you in that hell, and you just staying there, tolerating their mistreatment, you are the biggest fool on this planet. nobody deserves the right to ruin another person’s life, whether emotionally, financially or physically. you will meet some demons who argues instead that it is your fault that you let that person use you. 
honey, that’s the hard truth. the only truth that he spoke to me was that it was my fault that i allowed him to ruin me. honey, that’s the thing with demons. they don’t empathise. 
even today, when somebody is asking me to speak up against his atrocities, the hard truth is, that i can’t. even though i lost the battle and have deadly bruises that shall never heal, i have at least run to pick up the sword, and fight my way out of the battle.
i will be proud of myself for the rest of my life for successfully fighting my way out.

text:
today is the one year anniversary of the #metoo movement.  it is almost impossible to identify the first use of the moniker 'me too', which definitely predates 2017, but the viral growth of the hasthtag started october 15, 2017 in response to the sexual assault and sexual harassment allegations against some pretty powerful folks in the entertainment and media industry.  so powerful that the movement received time's person of the year award just a few months later.  the #metoo movement is not about politics, it is about solidarity with women who publicly accuse perpetrators of sexual assault/harassment and that is a good thing.  support all men and women in your life and stand with them when they have been wronged by others.  help them hold those guilty of predatory, unethical, illegal and manipulative behavior accountable.  please consider sharing this post on your timeline.  become the change you want to see. .
.
.
#bethechange | #socialjustice | #metoo

text:
l’avis de la presse 📄

après des mois d’attente, de bad buzz et de controverses en tout genre, l’épisode pilote du reboot de charmed, la série culte du début des années 2000 a enfin été diffusé. alors qu’en a pensé la presse ? le site première.fr salue des « personnages féminins forts, complexes, attachants et ancrés dans leur époque » ainsi que de beaux effets spéciaux, même s’il regrette un manque d’alchimie et de charisme concernant les trois actrices principales, sentiment partagé par programme-tv.net qui souligne cependant la prestation de sarah jeffery dans le rôle de maggie. pour le hollywood reporter, la série a « du potentiel, mais pas assez pour réellement charmer » alors que le journal vulture regrette « une célébration vide de la sororité et du pouvoir feminin ». plus positivement, le hollywood reporter apprécie une « plongée au cœur du mouvement #metoo » et ne doute pas que ce reboot pourra « coexister sans problème avec l’ancien charmed. »
#charmed #tvshow #serie #charmedreboot #sarahjeffery #madeleinemantock #meloniediaz

text:
[#metoomovement]
it was a year back. i read a post by a woman with the hashtag #metoo and when i asked her about that, she said, " women use this hashtag to speak about about the sexual harassment they have faced". and that's when i got to know about to know about this movement initially.

recently it has gained momentum and the feeds in social media is flooded up with this. i have seen a lot of women coming up and talking about this

so, what could you do?
no matter what gender you are, discuss about this to your female friends and any women in general and make them aware about this. it could move them forward and speak up.
one thing that hit me was, there were series of posts recently on facebook timeline and news  regarding women sharing their #metoo stories. many have spoken years and years later. who knows how many haven't opened up still? 
the point in starting a discussion is once a female talks about this,it will be surely a lead and many other women would talk too. to know what they have faced and what they have gone through, they should speak and we should let them speak. (let them speak) ➡➡so is it enough to start a discussion?
surely no!
everyone should be patient enough and broad minded to hear them. broad minded in the sense, we have seen cases where women are only blamed and shamed in scenarios of any abusement or harassment. is it her mistake getting raped or getting harassed or facing any kind of violence? there's no point in blaming the victim. people comment and pose up such questions to the #metoo stories,
"what's the proof?"
"what's the point in opening up after years later?"
and so on.. it's totally absurd in asking a woman the proof of violence. what else could be the proof than her body? and remember, harassments can happen verbally too. if in messages, screenshots can be a proof. if verbal abuse has happened face to face, what could she show for proof?
and the reason for opening up after years later is, as i said above victim blaming is the main reason. as the blaming pursues on, a women falls into a fear called 'fear of getting judged' and that stops her from opening up her issue. so its high time to stop blaming and hear them.

1. india

2. afghanistan

3. syria

4. somalia

5. saudi arabia

7. democratic republic of congo

8. yemen

9. nigeria

10. united states

for the first time, the us is considered one of the world's most dangerous countries.
the "most dangerous" list was compiled by the thomson reuters foundation.
550 experts in women's issues were surveyed by the foundation.
america joined the list after revelations from the #metoo movement.

text:
the urge to the masses is to maintain the sanctity of this movement and not let personal, religious or political vendettas and spurious stories dull the spark of this movement. the only resolution of this movement should be empowering more women who speak up, men who enact and justice that prevails. 
lastly, the me too movement is a double-edged sword where there is no generalization of victims or abusers. it goes without saying that the defendant is innocent until proven guilty and it also implies that every voice should be heard in a form of powerful message to change the system instead of individual agendas.

text:
i choose to live. .
.
.
this was one of my greatest mantras when i was dealing with my trauma. i had to wake up every day and choose to live. .
.
.
suicidal thoughts are just part of the package of effects that come from sexual abuse. i haven’t met one survivor who hasn’t had to deal with these dark and all encompassing thoughts. .
.
.
they isolate you. they hide you. and they try to take away the warrior within you. .
.
.
in my book i teach the tools i used to gain power over these dark thoughts. and also, i talk about my experience to help each reader know that they are not alone in the effect. you can live beyond these thoughts. and you can become the victor over them instead of the victim they make you become. .
.
.
i am so passionate about helping others with suicidal thoughts, i have decided to create a program designed to help those who struggle with this topic. if you are interested in joining me in the program, then follow me along @projectbreakthesilence. the first meeting is next week. ✨
.
.
.
and remember... this week i am giving away my digital course for free with the purchase of a book. link in bio😘😘

text:
ett år efter #metoo.
som många andra killar och män har vi känt en stor sorg och frustration i det uppvaknande som #metoo inneburit för dom flesta av oss. vi är många som inte förstått på riktigt hur utbrett det sexuella våldet är, hur många det är som varje dag utsätts för trakasserier och övergrepp som skapar djupa sår för livet, eller hur det samhälle vi lever i på olika sätt systematiskt upprätthåller och normaliserar attityder som utgör grunden för att övergrepp i alla dess former sker överhuvudtaget, samt att utsatta lever i sorg och skam, medan förövare går fria. vi är många som inte förstått på riktigt hur vi alla, inklusive oss "schyssta killar", genom att ha vuxit upp- och formats av kulturen, därmed har mycket vi måste(!) bidra med för att skapa förändring. främst förändringen i oss själva. vi tror stenhårt på att genom att möta unga killar med med våra föreläsningar där vi bryter ned skadliga maskulintetsnormer, med vår egen sårbarhet som grund, sår många frön för just förändring. vi tror lika mycket på att det medmänskliga samtalet, där stöttning för killars psykiska hälsa även har stark koppling till andra stora samhällsproblem- inklusive det sexuella våldet. för det är ju exakt det som det handlar om. om vi aktivt jobbar för att utveckla vår empatiska förmåga för både oss själva och andra kommer världen se annorlunda ut. 💙
.
tack till alla er kvinnor som med ilska, sorg, ödmjukhet, respekt och sunt jävla förnuft orkat(och inte orkat) göra den här revolutionen till just det- en revolution. vi har alla också @fattanu och många fler att tacka för att vi nu har en samtyckeslag som kan forma en ny kultur. där alla får får lära sig vad samtycke faktiskt är - och att det alltid ska finnas ett likamedtecken mellan samtycke och sex. en samtyckeskultur, helt enkelt!
tack också till alla er killar, män, ickebinära som använt era plattformar till att inte bara prata om förändring, utan även har skapat förändring- på riktigt.
.
nu fortsätter vi titta inåt, stötta, lyssna, peppa, och prata om allt vi har att vinna på att hjälpas åt att för att göra den här knappnålen i universum vi kallar "jorden" till en bättre plats - för oss alla.💙
kärlek.

text:
vi är rrriotsamba - en feministisk musikförening för transpersoner, kvinnor och icke-binära som spelar slagverk! föreningen består av banden @oyarrriotsamba, @rrriotsambasarava och @feministas_acidas. vi spelar en mängd olika rytmer, allt från afro-latinamerikanska som samba reggae och afoxé, till rytmer som vi själva tagit fram och utvecklat.
. rrriotsamba startade 2008 i stockholm och har genomfört en mängd häftiga spelningar sedan dess: förtrupp åt #tystnadtagning på guldbaggegalan, öland roots, musikhjälpen, invigning av konstverket "systrar utan gränser" i fittja, f!-stivalen, pride, statement festival och många demonstrationer, karnevaler och fester runtom i landet. rrriotsamba håller också kurser och workshops i feministiskt slagverk.
.
det håller även på att starta upp ett rrriotsamba i norrköping, och såklart vi i göteborg! ibland har vi även gemensamma spelningar då alla banden sammanstrålar, som ni kan se på sista bilden.

text:
++feminismus pt 2++
.
die care-arbeit umfasst existenziell notwendige aufgaben, wie die versorgung von kindern und älteren menschen, aber auch den haushalt zu führen. diese arbeit wird in der regel gar nicht oder sehr schlecht bezahlt.
.
die frau soll sich also traditionell um die familie und das haus kümmern, während der mann die  lebensgrundlage schaffen soll. doch mittlerweile sollen auch frauen gleichzeitig noch als lohnarbeiterinnen dem kapital dienen. frauen sind also einer doppelten ausbeutung ausgesetzt. einmal als lohnabhängige zusammen mit allen anderen, und zum anderen explizit als frau durch die notwendigkeit der reproduktion. .
hinzukommt, dass frauen durchschnittlich für den gleichen beruf immer noch weniger geld bekommen als männer, und bei gleicher qualifikation seltener eingestellt werden, meistens im teilzeit- oder niedriglohnsektor tätig sind. genannte gründe sind häufig kinder, wenn auch noch nicht vorhandene. außerdem wird angenommen, dass sich der mann durch die gesellschaftlich vorgeschriebenen eigenschaften besser in der berufswelt zurecht findet. diese gründe führen dazu, dass es, selbst wenn ein mann* nicht alle oben genannten eigenschaften erfüllt, in der berufswelt von vorteil ist, biologisch ein mann zu sein.
.
frauen werden also aufgrund ihres geschlechts in den für sie vorgesehenen bereich der sehr schlechten oder unbezahlten care-arbeit zurückgedrängt, welcher nur die spitze der ausbeutung darstellt. .
frauen verrichten weltweit 2/3 aller gesellschaftlich notwendigen aufgaben, erhalten dafür 1/10 des lohns und verfügen lediglich über 1/100 aller produktionsmittel. damit geht eine soziale unterordnung und eine ökonomische abhängigkeit der frau einher.
.
fortsetzung folgt .

text:
"as more people have found the courage to break through shame and speak about woundedness in their lives, we are now subjected to a mean-spirited cultural response, where all talk of woundedness is mocked. the belittling of anyone's attempt to name a context within which they were wounded, were made a victim, is a form of shaming. it is psychological terrorism. shaming breaks our hearts. all individuals who are genuinely seeking well-being within a healing context realize that it is important to that process not to make being a victim a stance of pride or a location from which to simply blame others. we need to speak our shame and our pain courageously in order to recover. addressing woundedness is not about blaming others; however, it does allow individuals who have been, and are, hurt to insist on accountability and responsibility both from themselves and from those who were the agents of their suffering as well as those who bore witness. constructive confrontation aids our healing." -bell hooks #wip #sketch .
.
.
.

text:
y sentir el miedo,el asco.
la impotencia más grande, porque tu fuerza no es la suya, más cuando está fuera de sí por "sentirse machito".
y oler ése perfume que tanto te repugna sobre tu piel,y ésas babas buscando tu cuerpo.
notar tu cabeza atravesar un grueso cristal,con el temor al "efecto guillotina".
no poder vivir tu amor verdadero sin miedo,pues una vez más puede alcanzarte con las ruedas de un vehículo,para después desaparecer entre la marabunta.
y ésta mierda de justicia.
ésta puta justicia, que tan sólo se mira el ombligo.
y de momento lo puedo hacer saber, que mañana dios⭐tal vez me regale un nuevo día.
pero tal vez igualmente,las leyes me lo arrebaten por ni tan siquiera "ponerse en marcha".
pd: no dejes de denunciar, aunque caiga en saco roto.
tal vez tus seres queridos,puedan llegar a conseguir la justicia que a tí te fue negada.
#noesno
#metoo

text:
#mybestlife. a lot of people are talking about this now on social media #metoo and #womensrights and within this we’ve seen a lot of beautiful, vulnerable, thought-stoking, soul-stirring remedies through storytelling.

we’ve also witness some confusion between what is *divine feminine* and what it means to be male or female or otherwise identified... meaning our very human (read: ego) responses as triggers are being reactivated.

we are all children of the earth and carry both energies along our axis points that surpasses physical anatomy or gender association.

that said, there’s also some real shit going down in this world and whenever there’s a draw back on the arrow, it’s an opportunity to propel forth new perspective, create healing paradigm and enter into the future of what our planet can be.

so, what exactly does it mean to be people?

why are we here?

and most importantly, how can we live a more sacred life?

join me and documentary storyteller andreas tonight at 8pm with our brothers and sisters for insightful unity on what this looks like and how we may work together.

8 pm est live *tonight* zoom link in the bio @theliftedheart 
please share, we welcome conversation for healing divine feminine and masculine energies as we explore human nature as both creatures and creators of our own environment 🧝‍♀️🧝‍♂️what are your thoughts on healing our planet, starsoul earthwalkers? 
swipe for more info. 
all perspectives are welcome, in a respectful way. video goes live at 8pm. 
image by jill wintersteen masucline feminine mars.jpg  https://zoom.us/j/937969892

text:
fair apparel. was a sector within fair market. that included t-shirts designed by women artists and designers that respond to this particular socio-political moment. the t-shirts were included as works of art in and of themselves or as artifacts of social and art historical movements that deepen our understanding of feminism and contemporary creative art movements.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
artists included were otherwild x herstory with the future is female t-shirt, zoila darton-word agency with creator shirt, bella doña, tatyana fazlalizadeh, and guerrilla girls.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non traditional venue.

fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
meet kaitlin⠀
--⠀
“dear katy (better known as tate),⠀
⠀
throughout your life you’re going to struggle in so many ways, that’s just part of being human. but for the most part there will be people to help guide you along the way. i’m reporting back to you as the 27- year-old version of yourself to share the advice on the one struggle you’ve faced the most in your life but have never been able to get advice about: how to be a mixed race woman in today’s world.”⠀
--⠀
