october is stop bullying month
*
i've been the target of bullying throughout my life.  when i was a child i was bullied for being 'weird'. i would be called a freak (until i liberated that word and found power in it). i was different and i didn't fit in anywhere i went.  as an adult i was bullied by an employer who did everything she could to take advantage of me.  she picked fights and created drama.  no matter your age i bet you know a bully. *
if you are being pushed around by a bully i urge you to stand up.  look for people who can support you.  build a community of supporters behind you.  but at the same time, don't forget that bullies are people too.  a lot of times they don't know how to express themselves is a positive way, and thusly end up taking their feelings of isolation etc out on other people. *
what are you doing this month to combat bullying in your school, workplace or community?
*
#stopbullying #antibullying #compassion #empathy #notavictim #metoo #timesup #cometogether #unite #bestrong #wearestrongertogether #elevate #elevateyourmind #stepup #standup

text:
mary elizabeth garrett, born in 1854 in baltimore, was the daughter and youngest child of john w. garrett, president of the baltimore & ohio railroad.  john garrett was known as the “railroad king”, a very wealthy man who was also celebrated as a first-class philanthropist, an abolitionist and a confidant of u.s. president abraham lincoln.  as mary’s two older brothers ascended into the garrett family businesses, she was left to find other interests, not surprisingly because in the late 1800s the corporate world, like the academic world and the voting booth, were glass ceilings to all women.  when john garrett died, mary inherited a large estate including several family properties, and eventually parlayed her wealth into philanthropy.  garrett used her intellect, connections and money to advance the cause of women’s suffrage; she also endowed bryn mawr college, and finally she played a critical role in the founding of johns hopkins hospital and johns hopkins school of medicine.

mary garrett was romantically involved with carey thomas, forced to hide their lesbian romantic relationship, running under the radar of 19th century mores.  on account of the low profile garrett was forced to adopt, the outside world knew little what mary had accomplished, the press instead having unfairly labeling her as america’s wealthiest spinster.  the same held true of carey thomas, quietly building bryn mawr college into one of the finest female colleges in the country.  bryn mawr graduate student louise saunders said it best when in 1897 she quipped of thomas: “it was above all, contact with her, contagion of the incomparable energy of her spirit, that lighted our spark also to flame. we anted to work hard, passionately, professionally, because we saw her working more passionately, more professionally than we." visit my blog at johnbershofmd.com

text: alone in the car with my younger son, today, i pretended to take credit for saying something fantastic, a quote which actually came directly from him.  he was like: "mawm,  i said that, not you." in all seriousness, with a straight face i replied; "nah-aaaaah, i am totally the one who said it." he was rightly disturbed- i admitted to playing and went on to share about about gas-lighting--how it can make a person feel crazy when someone repeatedly insists that things are different from how they know them to be.  i explained how gas-lighting is a real thing that some people do- and that it is a form of abuse.  he recalled how his bully did that to him in 4th grade(which he then began doing  relentlessly to his brother(we have nearly fully recovered over the course of a year)) i explained how it is especially troublesome when a person who is older or in a position of authority, whom is believed to be trustworthy, does this to a person who must depend on them.  the person being gaslit will begin to doubt everything, lose trust first in themselves, and then in others.  and that is an impossibly scary way to be in the world.  depression and anxiety often result and can sometimes be healed.  i stopped with that. #monsters #silenttreatment #ghost #hopeless #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth

text:
end violence against women and girls -  one in three women and girls experience violence in their lifetime—that is one too many. it happens in every country and every society. it happens at home, in schools, on the streets, at work, on the internet and in refugee camps. it happens during war, and even in the absence of war. too often, it is normalized and goes unpunished.

no matter where violence against women happens, what form it takes, and whom it impacts, it must be stopped. the promise of the sustainable development goals—to leave no one behind—cannot be fulfilled without ending violence against women. #rape #blackwomen #blackwomenbeingrape #friendsofhaiti2010 #lesamisdhaiti2010 #foh2010 #metoo

text:
don't let your loyalty become slavery!
so today i'm going to put light on an issue that 85% of women face but they fail to speak about it due to the fear of being judged & for other reasons. abuse ! as soon as we hear this word , the only thing we think about is the physical abuse, but abuse comes in many forms - it's not just physical , it can be- sexual, verbal, emotional, psycological,financial or cultural.
.
today i proudly say that i am a #survivor of verbal,emotional & psycological abuse. and these are one of the most lethal forms of abuse that kills confidence, creativity & individuality. they include insults and attempts to scare, isolate, or control you. it's also often a sign that physical abuse may follow. there were times when i was heartbroken, scared. i had a lot of anxiety, i was worried. i felt weak & had no idea how i was ever going to come up with the strength. but i just closed my eyes, & took a blind leap. i knew i had to get out of there.
.
learn to identify the difference. a healthy relationship will never require you to sacrifice your dignity or your dreams. and love is about giving freedom & power, not about gaining control or possession. when people treat you like they don't care, believe them. but put a stop to it right now. never forget that walking away from something unhealthy is brave.
.
don't let someone who did wrong make you think there's something wrong with you. don't devalue yourself because they didn't value you. know your worth even if they don't. believe in yourself, you survived the abuse. you're going to survive the recovery. don't judge yourself by what others did to you.
.
it's not the bruises on the body that hurt. it is the wound of the heart & the scars on the mind. there are wounds that never show on the body that are deeper and more hurtful than anything that bleeds. i realized that i was not worthless, i was unappreciated.
.
and i am not what happened to me, i am what i choose to become.

text:
end violence against women and girls -  one in three women and girls experience violence in their lifetime—that is one too many. it happens in every country and every society. it happens at home, in schools, on the streets, at work, on the internet and in refugee camps. it happens during war, and even in the absence of war. too often, it is normalized and goes unpunished.

no matter where violence against women happens, what form it takes, and whom it impacts, it must be stopped. the promise of the sustainable development goals—to leave no one behind—cannot be fulfilled without ending violence against women. #rape #blackwomen #blackwomenbeingrape #friendsofhaiti2010 #lesamisdhaiti2010 #foh2010 #metoo

text:
it's time we start raising our daughters differently. it's time we start telling them they can be anything they want to be. it's time we start telling them they can love fashion and kick ass at calculus. it's time we start telling them that if they love to write, they're not just creative, they can be pulitzer award-winning journalists. that if they love to care for their dolls, they're not just made to mother, they can be doctors and nurses and therapists.
so that some day, someday there will be no need for #metoo movements. so that some day, they too can run the world. so that some day, they don't need to ask for anyone's permission.
so please. please tell them that they are smart. that they can achieve anything they set their heart to. push them higher, nudge them further. encourage them. 
help them grow their wings, not clip them.
.
📷 @moniquephoto
.
.
.
#enoughisenough #itstime #timesup #bigbattlesahead #girls #weruntheworld #highereducation #parenting #raisingdaughters #stepmom

text:
(pune, india)
“i used to take science workshops for kids, because of which i became friends with a lot of young students. i’m really easy to talk to, so they felt comfortable with me. soon, i realized that most of them were curious about the opposite gender and the idea of sex. but since it’s such a ‘hush hush’ topic, there was nobody to give them accurate information.
this made me wonder – if these kids couldn’t talk about a ‘first kiss’ they’d loved, how would they talk about a kiss that wasn’t consensual? children have no idea how to deal with stalking, contraception, incest, abuse, consent….usually indian parents are so involved in their kids’ lives, yet they’re clueless about these things and choose not to talk about it. 
which is why, i decided to write a book called, ‘let's talk about guys girls and sex’. i wanted to include real life stories in it, and when i asked around, i was shocked that there were so many people who’d had traumatizing sexual experiences. 
i met a 60-year-old lady who still hasn’t dealt with the fact that she’d been abused by her relative when she was a child. he’s 90 years old now and she hasn’t confronted him about his actions! i even met a man, who was abused by his aunt when he was a kid, and he kept asking me ‘is this normal?’ because he’d never heard about males being abused by females. 
it was disheartening to see so many people carrying this burden around just because we as a society aren’t ready to talk about it. after our conversations, a lot of these people told me that they finally felt free and could now move on with their lives. i started writing this book for young adults, but i realized that a lot of older people were relating to it too. 
my son was in 10th grade when he read the first draft and i honestly feel that if i can talk to my teenage kids about it, then why can’t everybody else? i know they’re not going to tell me everything but atleast if i show them that i’m open to having such a conversation, then they’ll come to me if they ever get into trouble. they know that i’m here for them….and sometimes that’s enough.”

text:
en och samma dag i nyhetsflödet hos en kvällstidning. så många rubriker rörande våld mot tjejer och kvinnor. ett år efter #metoo.
känns onekligen som att det inte är läge att säga att vi kan ”lämna det här bakom oss nu”, eller ”vi ska inte överdriva hur stort problemet är”. och kanske ska vi för allas skull, inte förenkla hur man ska gå vidare med problematiken genom att så lätt hamna i ”men inte alla män” försvarsställning, och sedan stanna där, för det gäller ju inte en själv. en tanke bara.
.

ps. jag vet att inte alla män våldtar, trakasserar eller är våldsamma mot kvinnor. finns förstås så många fantastiska killar och män, bland majoriteten. men är inte mängden män som faktiskt gör det rubrikerna skriver om skäl nog för alla dessa fina män att vilja agera för att det ska kunna bli någon ändring i statistiken? eller ska vi fortsätta se problemlösning i de här frågorna mest som uppmaningar till tilltänkta offer att inte ”gå ut själv på kvällen”, ”klä sig för utmanande”, ”tappa koll på vad du dricker”? alltså lägga mycket ansvar att hitta lösningar på de som är utsatta.
.
.

text:
💥 dubbelt så många samtal om sexuella övergrepp - ett år efter #metoo 💥
. 
den 15 oktober 2017 spred sig #metoo som en löpeld genom sverige och världen. sedan dess har mycket hänt. omvärlden har – stundtals – tagit tjejernas berättelser på allvar, men många vittnar fortfarande om att det är svårt att berätta om sina upplevelser. en del tjejer hittar till tjejzonen och får ofta för första gången berätta utan att bli dömda.
. 
sedan #metoo startade för ett år sedan har antalet samtal om sexuella övergrepp och våld dubblerats i vår jourchatt.
. 
vi är så klart glada att så många modiga tjejer börjat prata om vad de upplevt, och lastat över skulden och skammen där den hör hemma – hos förövaren. men samtidigt har samhället, rättssystemet och killarna en hel del jobb kvar att göra! 😤
. 
stöd vårt arbete
bidra till att fler tjejer får sin röst hörd! stöd vårt arbete genom att swisha din gåva till 90 02 072.
. 
tusen tack! 🙌💕

text:
romance de bill clinton y mónica lewinsky no constituyó abuso de poder, dice hillary

hillary clinton dijo que el romance que su marido bill sostuvo hace dos décadas con monica lewinsky, una becaria de la casa blanca, no constituyó un abuso de poder, y que su esposo hizo bien en no renunciar a la presidencia ante el escándalo.

aquel episodio, que derivó en un juicio político a bill clinton, vuelve a estar bajo la lupa pública en la era #metoo: se cuestiona si la posición de un presidente y de una becaria no hacen imposible considerar que una relación sea consensuada.

algunos, como la senadora de nueva york kirsten gillibrand, dijeron que bill clinton debió renunciar tras ser sometido a un impeachment por haber mentido sobre su relación con lewinsky a fines de 1998, impulsado por el congreso dominado por los republicanos.

romance de bill clinton y mónica lewinsky no constituyó abuso de poder, dice hillary
pero la exprimera dama y excandidata presidencial hillary clinton dijo el domingo en cbs estar en desacuerdo. “de ninguna manera”, respondió al ser consultada si su esposo debió haber renunciado.

presionada sobre si la relación con la becaria fue un abuso de poder, la también exsecretaria de estado afirmó: “no, no”, y puntualizó que lewinsky, que tenía 22 años en aquel momento, “era una adulta”. “hubo una investigación y todo resultó, como creo, en el lugar correcto”, agregó.

en 1999, el senado sometió al presidente clinton a un juicio político que duró un mes y que no consiguió la mayoría de dos tercios para destituirlo.

para más información acceder a http://curiosodigital.com.do/

the story and the characters drag you in and get you right in the feels. you immediately feel like you are there. you are part of every scene...you feel angry, pissed off, sad, hurt, beat down and alone. 
i picked this up thinking it was a story about hockey. maybe like the olympic hockey team and their over coming the odds or something. but man was i wrong, it is a story about life and every shitty detail of it.  heart wrenching and well written. 
must read book. don't pass this one by.

text: on oct. 15, 1991, despite sexual harassment allegations by anita hill, the senate narrowly confirmed the nomination of clarence thomas to the u.s. supreme court, 52-48. a strikingly similar scenario unfolded recently when brett kavanaugh was confirmed 51-49 as a supreme court justice, despite sexual assault allegations against him by 3 women. one of his accusers, christine blasey ford, whom like hill, testified in front of the senate judiciary committee about her allegations. //📸➡️ ap // #usa #america #anitahill #christineblaseyford #metoo #brettkavanaugh #clarencethomas #donaldtrump #politics #supremecourt #history

let her be herself, dare not to tame her!

text:
this isn't a confession post.
for the past few days, we have been witnessing shocking revelations regarding sexual harassment faced by women in the entertainment industry.
many shocking names have come out. the starting point of this chain reaction was a famous case nearly a month back. we witnessed various kinds of reactions from the public. very few trusted the victim and stated that this is merely a publicity stunt.
well, i would like to tell people something:
1. being sexually harassed be it in a verbal or non-verbal way is a very disturbing moment in an individual's life (both men and women).
2. some incidents are so etched in our memories that no matter how many years pass by, those horrifying moments never go away.
3. every individual has a different capacity to react to or face a particular situation. if you don't find a thing offending or if you are strong enough to fight back then that doesn't mean each one of us is capable of doing that.
4. sometimes the strongest of people freeze during such a horrible situation and this is a fact.
5. it takes a lot of courage (a lot, really!) to stand up and speak about it and deal with the reactions it will trigger. many are still struggling to deal with it, many are still not okay to talk about it, many are still afraid to take out the particular name and shame them because somewhere they blame themselves for such incidents.
.
this scenario is applicable both in the case of men and women. i know some of my guy friends being harassed and still keeping quiet about it.
i'm not against men today, i'm against this predator-prey culture which is affecting both sexes alike. when someone comes out with their story, instead of silencing them we should listen to them. if you're unsure about the case, give the benefit of doubt to the victim. it takes immense courage and motivation to get out of that trauma.
... continued in first
comment
.
social by misha suman (@sumanmisha)
.

text: i recently got to discuss something i am extremely passionate about on a podcast. this interview is much less about acupuncture and much more about how experiencing trauma effects our bodies, our relationships and our communities. my hope is that approaching people in a trauma informed and healing centered way survivors can first feel empowered to trust themselves and than eventually repair safe boundaries with other people.  i want to thank my teachers and mentors for sharing your wisdom and hard work with me, i hope my words did you proud as i continue to learn every day. to my patients who have courageously walked the path after unspeakable acts of violence and allowed me to be a small part of your healing, you are an inspiration. to any person who has experienced trauma, whether from sexual assault or otherwise, i hope that you find strength in knowing you are not alone in your recovery, you are not what happened to you and are loved for everything that you are. ❤️ (link in bio)

text:
we are happy finally to announce our amazing news! awakenings will be partnering with tattoo shops around chicago to raise money for our upcoming year as well as providing safe, healing spaces and opportunities for people to reclaim their bodies through the art of tattooing. .
"as a survivor myself, tattooing has been crucial to my healing. two summers ago, i was entirely lost and felt as though my body was not my own. i made the decision to get one of my favorite barbra kruger quotes tattooed on my arm in an act of reclaiming my body. to this day, it is a constant reminder of the things i hold true. i want to thank @cknoxtattoo for being such a kind, empathetic, and strong person as well as an amazingly talented tattoo artist. thank you for our multiple sessions of feeling alive, empowered, and seen. thank you for helping me put on these flash events and continuing to support survivors of sexual" - kaitlin lynch (awakenings' social media and marketing coordinator)
.
we are still in the works of securing dates for other studios; however, we are very pleased to announce that on october 28th, animal farm will be hosting a flash event as well as evoke on november 11! thank you to these giving studios for your willingness to give! see their individual pages for more details.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: idag är det ett år sedan #metoo startade. i nordea har vi välkomnat rörelsen som ger oss anledning att arbeta ännu hårdare för ett arbetsklimat där sexuella trakasserier aldrig ska förekomma. vi har tagit fram ett verktyg som vi kallar ”let's talk!” för att alla team i nordea ska kunna föra en dialog om gränser och vad som är okej och inte på våra arbetsplatser. vi har dessutom tagit fram riktlinjer för hur vi förebygger trakasserier och andra oacceptabla beteenden, samt hur vi agerar om det sker. tack också till alla fantastiska medarbetare som varje dag bidrar till en inkluderande arbetsmiljö där alla trivs, är trygga och respekterar varandra! #inclusivenordea (syntolkning: mattias och bosse utanför nordea i stockholm)

to save #america we must end the #republican protection and enabling of the unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. election day is nov. 6, 2018... register! #vote! don’t stay silent. know what people in office are planning for your life. and ladies, for your bodies. ——> your vote matters! though he lost the popular vote to #hillaryclinton, donald trump owes his victory in the electoral college to three states he won by the smallest number of votes: pennsylvania, wisconsin, and michigan. so it's fair to say that the 2016 presidential election was decided by about 77,000 votes out of than 136 million ballots cast. according to the final tallies, trump won pennsylvania by 0.7 percentage points (44,292 votes), wisconsin by 0.7 points (22,748 votes), michigan by 0.2 points (10,704 votes). three key states—all lost by less than 1% each. it’s math… if we all get out and vote… we can start to end the crazy… investigate… #trump #russia #washingtondc #lovetrumpshate #dumptrump #nevertrump #msnbc #cnn #foxnews #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #maga #makeamericagreatagain #plannedparenthood #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #resist

text:
#페미니즘 #페미니스트 #feminism #feminist #metoo #withyou #미투 #꽃뱀 #만물꽃뱀설 #이중잣대 #남녀차별 #걸레 #창녀 아니면 #성녀
무고죄 주장하며 여자가 꽃뱀이라는 글 질리도록 많이 보고 경험했다. 남자가 여자 탓을 해도 여자는 꽃뱀이 되고, 여자가 남자 탓을 해도 여자가 꽃뱀이 된다.
-
'2016년도 대법원 사법연감’을 보면 한 해 동안 법원에 접수된 성범죄 건수와 성범죄 건수와 무고죄 건수를 알 수 있다. 전국지방법원에 접수된 형사공판 사건재판을 죄명별로 보면, 성범죄 건수는 총 15,561건으로 집계됐다. 
이 중 1심에서 무죄를 받은 건수는 15,561건 중 327건(2%)이다.
무고죄 건수는 1,511건이다. 이 가운데 성범죄 관련 무고죄는 많아봐야 327건이다. 따라서 전체 접수된 성범죄 사건 가운데 무고죄가 성립할 수 있는 가능성은 2% 이하라고 볼 수 있다.
-
또한 성폭력 피해자 건수는 29,357건이다.
이 중 남성 피해자는 1,478건(5%), 여성 피해자는 26,116(89%)이다. 성별미상은 1,763건(6%)이다.
-
[은진 기자, “‘미투’ 확산에 ‘꽃뱀’ 공포?... 통계 근거 없다.”, <시사위크>, 2018. 03. 19.]
-
98%의 성범죄가 있어도 2%의 무고죄에 면죄부를 얻으려는 꽃뱀무새들. 이래놓고 성폭력 여성피해자가 89%가 되는데도 자기들을 잠재적 가해자 취급한다고 뭐라 하는 건 어떻게 받아들여야 하는 거람?
2%는 자기들에겐 큰 숫자면서 우리들의 89%는 피해망상 취급하네? 
둘 중 하나만 혀.

text:
idag är det ett år sedan tarana burkes metoo-rörelse väcktes på nytt av alyssa milanos tweet. en tweet som ledde till en löpeld av vidriga vittnesmål från kvinnor över hela världen.
.
raderna om #metoo i @karlsson_maj 1 maj-tal är fortfarande lika aktuella:
.
"vi lever i en tid där rasister använder använde kvinnors kroppar som slagträn för rasism. där världens mäktigaste män gör sig lustig över att han utsatt kvinnor för sexuella övergrepp. men en tid som håller på att gå mot sitt slut.
.
för över en natt. med en tweet av alyssa milano inspirerad av tarana burke utlöste en feministisk tsunamivåg som med brutal styrka svepte över hela världen. en tweet som förvandlades till ett enormt avgrundsdjupt vrål som skapade en jordbävning genom hela patriarkatet. 1000-tals kvinnor som med gemensam kraft bröt den tystnadskultur som ekat genom generationer av kvinnor för att män skall behålla sin makt.
.
det är en revolution som genomförts med en enorm och massiv kärleksarmé av systerskap. en helt fredlig revolution med våra vittnesmål som enda vapen med en kraft så brutal att den skakat hela världen rakt in i människors egna samveten.
.
nu är tiden förbi där vi kommer låta oss tystas. vi kommer inte vara tysta om hur det känns när våra kroppar blir studerade och kommenterade med sådan gränslöshet att vi själva känner skam inför våra egna kroppar.
.
vi kommer inte vara tysta om att våra arbetsplatser allt som oftast är brottsplatser. där vi kvinnor i vårt vardagliga arbete blir kommenterade, trakasserade, terroriserade och där vi blir straffade med att vi får kliva ner. att vi fått kliva undan.
.
och de ska lyssna på våra vidriga vittnesmål om vilken fruktansvärd skräck och smärta vi fått uppleva när en man med tvång tagit på och våldfört sig på oss. trots att vi sagt nej. trots att vi skrikit på hjälp. trots att våra kroppar blivit helt stela för att vi frusit till is i ren skräck.
.
med vårt gemensamma vittnesmål har vi synliggjort att det som sker har hänt mig, kvinnan du möter i affären, hon som möter dig på sjukhus, förskola eller är din chef. nu har vi visat exakt hur patriarkatets verkliga ansikte ser ut.” #metoo #patriarkatetfallerinomdinlivstid #vgbg #vgbgftw
name: Vänsterpartiet Göteborg

text:
i’ve been pretty quiet on social media the last week or two. this past week i had one of the worst days i’ve had in my ed journey since getting out of treatment. i just couldn’t get in a good headspace. i just couldn’t. i found out a dear friend of mine from treatment was in the hospital and in pretty rough shape. it’s always scary knowing someone who has the same bug in the system of their brain as you do is struggling. it makes struggling seem more imminent than possibility for me. 🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤•••🖤
some controversy over the #metoo movement and people’s lack of knowledge or compassion for those going through it really got me in a bad place as well. 
i think a lot of us are struggling with how to keep our warrior faces on in the midst of such a blood bath of unkindness and cruelty in our world today. we don’t always feel we can stand up against it. sometimes it’s hard to keep pushing forward, muddling through all the muck. 💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙💙this week, white angelica- a blend by young living- has been my shield. i rub it on my chest, put some in my hair, on my wrists. use it in unison with frankincense and wow. god is so good. 🌴🌱🍊🌳🌺🌵🌼🌲🌸🌾💐🍁🌻🌴🍋i am so thankful to my jesus for creating plants and trees and roots and fruits and berries and bushes and shrubs that produce such powerful oils and resins. god gave us so many tools to take care of ourselves and i truly believe that these plant- based oils are one of his greatest gifts for our mind, body, spirit and heart. 🚀🚀🚀for those of you on any kind of mental health recovery journey or any of you on a battlefield with your emotions, i’m in the trenches with you and i know your war. prayer and good vibes and all the oily tools to y’all 🤟🏽

text:
avoiding #danger to survive is an unconscious reflection in all species. when a person faces a sudden threat to their life, the sophisticated intellectual abilities are useless. to detect and elude the threat, the brain has immediate mechanisms of reaction that include running away, fighting, screaming, paralyzing.

although the best technique to avoid facing an attack is to run, with ester we explore how to modify the trigger with involuntary preprogrammed reflexes, which operate before the cerebral cortex decides the course of action. in this way ester increases her chances of surviving an #attack 😁💪👍. . .

evitar el #peligro para sobrevivir es un reflejo inconsciente en todas las especies. cuando una persona enfrenta una amenaza súbita contra su vida, las sofisticadas capacidades intelectuales resultan inútiles. para detectar y eludir la amenaza,  el cerebro dispone de mecanismos inmediatos de reacción que incluyen huir, pelear, gritar, paralizarse. 
aunque la mejor técnica para evitar enfrentarse a un ataque es correr, con ester exploramos cómo modificar el detonante con reflejos preprogramados involuntarios, que operan antes de que el córtex cerebral decida el curso de acción. de esta manera ester aumenta sus posibilidades de sobrevivir a un #ataque 😁💪👍. .

#fight #selfdefense #drill #knive #cuchillo #defensapersonal #metoo #couplegoals #coupletraining #taichi #yoga #martialarts #artesmarciales

text:
we walk to breath
fill our senses with peace
but today we talk to speak
now our voices filled with unease 
we are displeased we do resist 
to  the leaders of this office 
how can we sit and let them take it 
ruin the americanism we made it 
we need  change 
from now on forward 
so we can end all the oppression
of the poor by the rich
of the color they don’t seek
of the women they found meek
of the ones surviving  week after week 
we must show that we are one
we must act undivided this once
we must vote, hear our voices all at once 
it’s our country it’s our town
we must overcome , turn it around
we must help each other each one
there is power in everyone
we must not let ourselves down.  #politicalartwork #politicalcompass #calltovote #callforchange2018 #artandpoliticsnow #abstract_art #artisansofsanfrancisco#sanfranciscowomenartists #artspansf#metoo #metoomovement #womenpower#votenovember2018

text:
aujourd'hui, c'est l'anniversaire du #metoo! 🕯❤
pour souligner l'occasion, nous avons créés deux modèles de chandails en collaboration avec l'osbl @jesuisindestructibleqc , qui est avant tout une plateforme web de témoignages pour les personnes victimes d’agressions à caractère sexuel.
pour chaque chandail vendu, 8$ seront remis à l'organisme afin de poursuivre leur mission d'information et de soutien.
depuis tant de générations, les femmes vivent toujours entre la peur des violences sexuelles et les conseils d’être constamment vigilantes. grâce à un mouvement comme celui-ci, je me sens de plus en plus confiante de léguer un monde plus outillé à mes filles.
il faut se protèger, s'informer et surtout dénoncer. merci je suis indestructible pour votre travail extraordinaire. 💗💗💗

text:
bollywood filmmakers vow not to work with proven sex offenders 
11 prominent female figures in the film industry have shared a note on social media signed and stating that they will no longer work with ‘proven sexual offenders’. this move comes as an auxiliary to the #metoo movement which is gaining momentum with  women joining hands, supporting each other and calling out perpetrators.

critically-acclaimed directors such as konkona sen sharma, nandita das, meghna gulzar, gauri shinde, kiran rao, reema kagti and zoya akhtar are among the eleven women filmmakers who have pledged their support to india's #metoo movement.

text:
sejak aktris tanushree dutta melaporkan aktor kawakan nana patekar atas kasus pelecehan seks beberapa waktu, kini satu persatu  para seleb bollywood mengikuti jejaknya. dan kemarin aktris 'stree', flora saini juga melaporkan sutradara vikash bahl atas penyerangan.

kini satu lagi seleb yang melaporkan rekan mainnya atas kasus pelecehan seks dan juga perkosaan.

dia adalah penulis-sutradara vinta nanda dan aktris sandhya mridul yang melaporkan aktor terkenal alok nath

vinta nanda baru-baru ini melaporkan aktor 'vivah' tersebut ke polisi dengan tuduhan  telah melakukan pelecehan seks 20 tahun lalu, saat keduanya bekerjasama dalam serial tv berjudul 'tara'. dia (alok nath) sama sekali tak terlihat menyesal. dia malah tersenyum sinis. padahal jika dia mau minta maaf, saya akan mempertimbangkan untuk membebaskannya. tapi sekarang saya akan terus melanjutkannya hingga akhir," tegas vinta

menurut vinta, alok nath tak hanya melecehkan (berbuat tak senonoh) pada dirinya saja, melainkan juga pada artis lain yang juga bermain dalam serial tv 'tara' yakni navneet nishan. namun saat itu, vinta dan juga navneet tak bisa berbuat banyak, karena alok adalah yang lebih senior

sedangkan aktris sandhya mridul menceritakan di akun twitter miliknya ketika ia dilecehkan saat syuting film televisi (zee) di kodaikanal.

di ftv tersebut ia berperan sebagai anak dari alok nath dan reema lagoo. saat itu selepas makan malam dan alok nath mabuk ia memaksa sandhya duduk didekatnya dan membuatnya tak nyaman. akhir nya aktor lain di film itu "sadar" dan membawa sandhya menjauh. "beberapa waktu selanjutnya saat break syuting alok nath selalu mabuk dan mencariku, ia menangis dan memelukku. aku sangat risih saat itu bahkan aku selalu ditolong reema lagoo. semua tim produksi memintaku memaafkannya. bahwa ia bintang besar sedangkan aku masih pemula" ungkap sandhya.

text:
warning : if you are a *pseudo* feminist then don't read further. 
dear #metoo
i have a question for you, will you answer me? please? 
actually i was just wondering that can males too use this hashtag? and if they'll do then will society believe them too? if they'll come up with their issues without any proof, will they be listened? 
i'm asking all these questions because i believe that everyone has a story to tell.
it's not compulsory that shit happens only with one gender. sometimes it can be a boy too.

just imagine a boy posting that he was raped. yes, there will be some people who'll believe him and will help him too but the majority of comments will go like : 1.
2.
3.
..
do i seriously need to mention some? hey come on, i know you already got me.

see i'm not against you, i know things start for a good and so did you. many hidden stories came in the picture. many genuine *humans* got justice. but the society in which we live, these things spread like a cancer. people just exaggerate everything. yeah, i agree it's not easy to use these things for publicity but believe me there are obviously some people who do it for the same.

most importantly, girls just keep their point in words, mind me just in words and we as a society believe them, why? because they are girls. this social media can ruin anyone's life/career and that too in a single day. don't you think that a girl can use this against a boy whom she hates, maybe who rejected her. we as a society say no means no, so same goes for the boys too, maybe there can be a boy who said no to a girl and to take revenge she can use you mr. #metoo, can't she?

everyone suffers! and everyone includes all the genders. i'm not disagreeing that girls don't suffer but with that i agree that boys suffer too. if a boy gains enough guts to raise his voice then not even all other boys will support him, agree?. p.s. - it wasn't intended to hurt anyone's feelings and sentiments, i respect you girls but with that i respect boys too or precisely you can say i respect humans.
by @ankita_jain_annie

text:
it is important to remember not to blame ourselves for the actions of others. survivors too often think they did something to deserve the violence they've endured. this is usually a response to #gaslighting. .
.
.
"gaslighting is an extremely effective form of emotional abuse that causes a victim to question their own feelings, instincts, and sanity,  which gives the abusive partner a lot of power (and we know that abuse is about power and control). gaslighting tends to happen very gradually in a relationship; in fact,  the abusive partner's actions may seem like harmless misunderstandings at first. over time,  however,  these abusive behaviors confuse, and a victim can become confused,  anxious, isolated,  and depressed." #nationaldomesticviolencehotline
.
.
abuse comes in many forms: physical, emotional, financial, sexual, spiritual, and technological. remember today and every day that there is nothing you or anyone has done to deserve it. #dvam .
.
.
thank you @traumaandco for your post, #christinaenevoldson author of #overcomingsexualabuse, and @ndvhofficial
.
.
#ithappens #endgbv #standwithsurvivors #standwithsakhi #breakthecycle #power #control #notyourfault #metoo #timesup #domesticviolence #abuse #desi  #southasian #community #support

text:
*an open letter to my voice*

hey,

i don't know if this would reach the correct address, but it's been way too long since i've been trying to find you and i'm clutching to every single straw that i can get a hold of just to stay afloat in the ocean of voices.

when did you decide to leave me exactly? was it when my uncle shut himself along with me in a room when i was four and couldn't fathom what we were doing there? all i remember is that it hurt. he taught me how to pinkie promise and i pinkie promised him that i won't tell anyone about our 'new game'. or was it when that elderly man in the train groped me while i was making my way to the washroom? he was of my grandfather's age and i thought it was a mistake. but when he did it again and looked approvingly at me, i felt sick and stayed in the washroom for the rest of the journey.

or was it when my date tried to force himself on me, despite my resistance? well, i remember murmuring a 'no'. but then, he didn't listen and i tried to reason it out with myself that it was meant to happen, that people do that when they are in love, that it was all fine.

or was it when my boss tried to inch his hand up my skirt during the presentation? it took me all my might to not shout there. after all, he had the upper hand there. my career could have been sabotaged. i was afraid. it's okay if people get afraid sometimes, right? it's okay if i stood under the shower for three hours that day just to get the feeling of his disgusting fingers off my body, right?

i quit my job after that. i haven't been on a date in ages. i don't have the guts to travel in trains. i make up random excuses so that i can avoid meeting my uncle. but those are only the instances of me running away from my experiences. i don't think i have the strength to run anymore.

all through the last week, i saw women like me voice their harrowing experiences very similar to mine. i saw them bare themselves and emerge stronger after that. they had voices; their voices merged into one single voice and that was where they got their strength from. (cont in the comments)

text: predators look for children who appear vulnerable and isolated. and, since our children spend a good portion of their day in school, this is often where predators look for their victims. therefore, parents and caregivers need to make it a point to visit your child's school to not only make your presence in your child's life known to potential predators, but also to break up patterns and routines that allow predators access to sexually abuse your child, and identify areas in which the school may need to improve policies, procedures and practices that place children at risk for abuse. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
for all those who say why are women speaking up now after a gap of many years let me tell you, you have failed to understand the #metoo movement.. its a movement for all to speak up and voice their trauma and fight a common battle. please shed the idea that women/girls are the only the victim of molestation and sexual assault men/boys too are victims of the same and if they start speaking up breaking the social typecast of masculinity, that will be the real victory for all of us as a race..

text:
the day my school
divided our skirt,
a poor child wore 
dupatta over her uniform.
we both had to hide
because boys could 
get distracted.
no, there were
no boobs in class.
there were chests
that were broad,
and chests concealed
in the misery of hating
oneself for everything
god had given.
i asked my friend why
we were supposed to
wear bras, and she said:
"so the guys don't notice
our breasts bounce,
and you are not supposed
to run that fast,
detain that jump
in your walk,
they can guess 
your size.
don't talk 
too loud,
only guys can 
imitate
and somehow,
don't let them know
how much a woman
you are, wear 
an extra slip to be 
less noticeable, maybe."
the poor girl just
left school
for womanhood.
i was asked to hate 
myself
and then invited
into a house
to sit with others
just like me
so that aunty
could break fast
by worshipping
the goddess who lived
in us.
i refused to give her 
my blessings.

i refuse to bless you.
i am a goddess all
through the year.
i will not bless you
for disrespecting 
and hiding
and hating
my body.
i killed mahishasur.
i killed raktabeej.
i did that with a sword.
i ran faster than you have
seen any one running.
i jumped higher with every
stroke of my knife,
i let my breasts bounce,
i let them feed,
i let them dance
in tandava with shiva.
i am the source of energy.
i am pride.
i am a roar that never dies.
i am deafening quietness.
i am life.
i am the irony of your sentiments.
you don't ask blessings
from a goddess you
don't approve in real life.
don't try me behind
the shiny dupatta
you so righteously
offer in exchange.
i am exposure of 
insanity and zen
and humanity
in feminine.
i am everything 
beautiful and 
everything
you don't see
in the girls
you call goddesses.
a teacher once told me
to shout every time
some one assaults 
me by the road.
if my quiet is their power,
i'll never stop roaring.
- nidhie saini

text:
#ohoreads milkman by anna burns, winner of the @manbookerprizes! "the day somebody mcsomebody put a gun to my breast and called me a cat and threatened to shoot me was the same day the milkman died. he had been shot by one of the state hit squads and i did not care about the shooting of this man. others did care though, and some were those who, in the parlance, 'knew me to see but not to speak to', and i was being talked about because there was a rumour started by them, or more likely by first brother-in-law,  that i had been having an affair with this milkman and that i was eighteen and he was forty-one...it had been my fault too, it seemed, this affair with the milkman."
.
during the irish troubles, a young woman tries to evade the sexual advances of a senior paramilitary figure called the milkman, who first begins harassing her while she is walking home reading. what burns does with language here is very intriguing - the sentences are long and fibrous, paragraphs stretching across pages; nearly nobody has names; all things are divided into "ours" and "theirs" - "the right butter. the wrong butter. the tea of allegiance. the tea of betrayal." experimental and eerily resonant in the #metoo era. link in bio to our booker feature, including reviews of all six titles (@beiyiss reviews milkman for us) #lookinglit
.
